title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions.
Saute in butter, celery and onion.
Add cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with oleo.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry n sour cream salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water; add bananas, pineapple with juice and strawberries.
Pour 1/2 into oblong dish; let set in refrigerator (leave other 1/2 on cabinet).
After first 1/2 sets, spread 1 pint sour cream on top and pour remaining Jell-O and return to refrigerator.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in flour; add flavoring.
Bake in greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans at 325° for about 1 hour.
This is a good cake to slice and serve with strawberries.

title: lemon fruit dip(by crystal light)
directions: Stir drink mix into yogurt in medium bowl until blended. Makes 3 cups.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: hershey pie
directions: Add marshmallows to milk; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Mix in whipped cream.
Add Hershey bar, grated.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Serve cold.

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 of the flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and shortening and mix well. Beat in remaining flour.
Cover with a damp cloth and store in refrigerator.
Punch down dough about twice a day (in the morning and before bed).
Dough will keep between one and two weeks. About 2 hours before baking, make out rolls in shape desired and place on greased pan.
Let rise in draft free, warm place covered with a dry cloth.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Squeeze juice from lemons and oranges; pour boiling water over cloves and let stand 10 or 15 minutes. Strain all and mix together. Sweeten to taste. Heat to boiling point and serve hot with thin slices of lemon. Any fruit juices are good to mix with this. Serves about 18 persons.

title: italian cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Place in a jar and store in refrigerator.
Shake well before using.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 3 layers.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Slice or cut longways.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand overnight, covered.
Pour off water.
Mix all other ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Pack pickles in pint jars.
Pour syrup over cucumbers.
Seal.
Process in water bath 5 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: basic fried woodchuck
directions: Cut woodchuck into slices 1/2-inch thick.
Mix beaten egg and milk.
Salt and pepper woodchuck slices and dip into mixture; roll in flour.
Place in hot oil and cook until golden brown, turning once.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together 1 cup salad dressing, 1 1/2 cups sour cream and Knorr mix, set aside.
Drain spinach and add water chestnuts and green onions.
Stir in mixture until well blended.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: pineapple parfait
directions: Soften ice cream.
In a separate bowl mix 1 cup hot water with Jell-O.
Add soft ice cream and mix.
Then add pineapple juice only and mix.
Refrigerate until it thickens.
Add pineapple and mix.
Pour into graham cracker crust pan.
Refrigerate until thick.
Slice and enjoy.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces. Place in a casserole dish. Layer the rest of the ingredients in order given. Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over the top, as you would frosting. Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 - 12 hours. At serving time, garnish with additional bacon and parsley.

title: chewy bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Add pecans; pour into a greased oblong baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes. Yields one loaf.

title: easy sugar cookie
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to mixture until smooth.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll into a small ball.
Press on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Mash flat with a glass dipped into sugar.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: buttery rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients together. Spoon into greased muffin pan half full.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes.

title: vegeburger
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Spoon onto hot frying pan and form patties 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick.

title: kiwi fruit blueberry salad
directions: Place lettuce on 4 individual plates.
Arrange kiwi fruit on lettuce and top evenly with blueberries.
Combine mayonnaise and next 3 ingredients.
Stir well.
Drizzle over salads and top with strawberries.
Serve immediately.

title: microwave cheesy chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Dip in butter, then in cracker crumbs.
Cook in microwave dish, covered with Saran Wrap.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook 1 minute.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour pans.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients 2 minutes; scrape bowl frequently.
(Batter will be very thin.)
With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake.

title: yummy orange balls
directions: Mix wafers, sugar and pecans.
Add melted butter and orange juice.
Roll into balls.
Freeze.

title: caesar dressing(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Combine dry mix, vinegar, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, water and Parmesan cheese.
Mix 2 minutes at high speed with electric mixer at high speed.
Continue mixing at high speed and slowly add oil.
Mix at high speed for 2 minutes until well blended. Keep refrigerated.
Make fresh; do not mix old dressing with freshly made dressing.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream shortening and granulated sugars together; add egg, mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hot crab meat
directions: Combine all ingredients, topping with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbling hot.

title: baked eggs
directions: Put in greased 9 x 12-inch square pan; refrigerate overnight. Bake 40 minutes at 350°; cut in squares and serve hot.

title: applesauce
directions: Pare, quarter and core 4 medium apples.
Combine apples, water and cinnamon stick.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Mash apples until smooth.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar.

title: jim's large chocolate fudge
directions: Mix and bring to a rolling boil the first 3 ingredients. Reduce heat and boil 5 minutes.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and place into a buttered pan.
Cool.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Cream cheese and sugar together.
Beat eggs until fluffy and add to mixture.
Add pineapple, drained and mix.
Fold in Cool Whip (thawed).
Put vanilla wafers on bottom.
Add some of the filling (mixture).
Repeat 2 to 3 more times.
Let filling be last on top and top it or sprinkle with chopped (finely) nuts.
Leave in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all together, salt and pepper to taste.
Add Italian salad dressing, the amount you want, mix again.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Let chill about 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: stuffed eggs and crab
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash yolks; combine with crab meat, celery, green pepper, salad dressing and sour cream, blending well.
Stir until well mixed.
Refill egg whites.
Chill until serving time.
Pretty served on lettuce garnished with paprika or parsley sprigs.

title: steak soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except butter and flour, in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours.
Make a paste of the melted butter and flour.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into crock-pot and stir until thickened.
Cook soup on high until thickened.

title: pink pear salad
directions: Chill pear halves.
Cut cherries into small pieces.
Soften cream cheese; add 1 tablespoon cherry juice, cherries and salt. Blend thoroughly.
Add pecans and mix well.
Heap cream cheese mixture into hollow of pears.
(Tint outside of pears with remaining cherry juice, optional.)

title: blender pancakes
directions: Wash, peel and cut up potatoes.
Pat dry with paper towels. Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover.
Press chop button for 10 seconds, stop.
Use spatula to push potatoes down if necessary. Spoon batter onto hot greased griddle, using about 1/4 cup for each pancake.
Brown on one side, then turn once to brown other side.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Grease Bundt pan and put desired amount of raisins (and/or) nuts on bottom.
Top with dinner rolls that have been cut in half. Mix dry ingredients (pudding, brown sugar and cinnamon) and sprinkle over dough. Pour melted margarine over top of all.
Cover pan with towel and let rise overnight in the oven.
Remove towel and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and invert on serving dish.
Let stand a few minutes, then remove pan. Delicious!

title: meat loaf in an onion
directions: Butter 2 slices of bread.
Put butter side next to the irons.

title: cream-style corn
directions: Cut tips of corn off cob, then scrape off corn from the cob to make 2 cups of corn.
Add milk, salt and margarine.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mountain mama's mudslide cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat with mixer until thick.
Spread on cream cheese mixture and top with Cool Whip.
Grate a Hershey bar and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Cook onion in water for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Heat milk, but don't let it boil.
Add soda to tomatoes.
Add tomato mixture slowly to milk.
Do not let mixture boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste and serve.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix beef and 3/4 jar sauce (to desired consistency).
In a glass loaf pan, place a layer of noodles, beef mix, then dot with cottage cheese and layer other cheeses. Continue layering, ending with cheeses.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until cheeses lightly brown.
Makes about 4 or 5 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Measure warm water into mixing bowl; add yeast.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing until smooth (add enough flour to handle easily, mixing with your hands now).
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Round up in greased bowl.
Let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again until almost double for desired rolls.
Roll dough; put into oblong pan (15 x 9-inch) and spread with 2 teaspoons softened butter; sprinkle with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Roll up tightly, beginning at wide side.
Seal well by pinching edges of roll together.
Stretch roll slightly.
Cut roll into 1-inch pieces; place a little apart.
Cover to let rise until doubled, 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: italian delight
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix all ingredients together; place in large casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in a medium pot.
Combine water, food coloring and oil and add.
Cook over medium heat and stir about 3 to 5 minutes.
It will look like a globby mess, but stay with it.
When it forms a ball in the center of the pan, turn it out and knead on a lightly floured surface.
Store in Ziploc bag.
Keeps for weeks!

title: mexican chicken mole
directions: Brown chicken in 1 teaspoon of oil in a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Remove.
Add remaining oil, carrot, celery and onion to skillet; saute until tender.
Add tomato sauce, broth, cocoa, sugar, pepper and cinnamon.
Bring to boiling.
Add chicken.
Lower heat and simmer, covered, 12 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together; pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or so.

title: fresh asparagus omelet
directions: Combine the eggs and milk in a small mixing bowl and beat lightly with a fork.
Cook asparagus, thyme, and basil in 1 tablespoon of margarine or butter in small saucepan for 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat and set aside. Melt 1/2 teaspoon margarine or butter in an 8 or 10-inch skillet. Pour in egg mixture and cook over medium heat.
As the eggs set, run a spatula round the edge of the skillet, lifting the eggs and letting the uncooked portion flow underneath.
When the eggs are set, but still shiny, remove them from the heat.
Spoon the cooked asparagus across center of the omelet.
Sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Fold in half.
Top with remaining cheese.
Makes 2 servings.

title: "punch" bowl
directions: Combine all ingredients together and serve.
Makes 1 bowl.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Drain.
Add milk, salt and pepper to taste, Velveeta cheese and ham cubes.
Microwave until cheese melts.
Mix well before serving.

title: crab stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs
in	half lengthwise; remove yolks and mash. Combine
yolks, crabmeat, celery, green pepper, salad dressing mix and sour cream; blend well.
Stir until well mixed.
Stuff egg white
with
crabmeat
mixture.
Chill until serving time. Yields 12 servings.

title: corn and tater soup(low calorie)
directions: Cook frozen corn as directed on package.
Do not drain. Combine all ingredients (except cheese) in pan and heat.
When hot, add cheese and stir until melted.
Makes 6 servings.
One serving equals 110 calories or 1 bread and 1/2 skim milk exchanges.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Deep fry wings in hot oil for 10 to 12 minutes, then drain. Mix all other ingredients and roll fried wings in sauce.
Place on baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
"Great with celery and Blue cheese."

title: hobo bread
directions: Soak raisins in
boiling
water.
Add soda. Stir, cover and let stand overnight.

title: holiday cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor. Process 2 minutes or till smooth. Spoon into serving bowl and chill at least eight hours or up to five days.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours at room temperature.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place layers of the vegetables in the order given in crock-pot.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Put the lightly browned ground beef on top of the celery.
Mix the tomato soup with the water; pour into crock-pot.
Cover and set to high for 4 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally.
(May cook on low for 6 to 8 hours, but vegetables may be a little hard.)

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Cool, peel and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook 2 cups cheese and butter until melted. Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper. Pour in potatoes and fold.
Pour into baking pan.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes. Add all other ingredients. Cook on high heat until potatoes are done.

title: pecan pie #3
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup and pecans.
Melt butter.
Add to rest of mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna and spinach casserole
directions: Grease a small casserole dish with fairly high sides.
In bottom, layer thawed and drained frozen spinach.
Mix 3/4 cup sour cream with the cooked rice and layer over spinach.
Flake tuna over rice.
Spread remaining sour cream over tuna and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Warm completely covered in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: frank and potato bake
directions: Reserve 3 franks; slice remaining franks and set aside.
In saucepan, stir milk into flour until smooth.
Add cheese; cook and stir until thickened and smooth.
Add onion and 1/2 teaspoon salt; fold cheese mixture into potatoes and sliced franks.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Half the reserved franks; arrange in pinwheel atop casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Top with parsley, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pan rolls
directions: Combine yeast and water.
Scald milk (using a double boiler). Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool.
Add 1 cup flour and mix well.
Add yeast mixture and egg.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and grease top of dough.
Cover and place in warm place.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours; punch down.
Shape in balls and place in 2 greased square pans.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Butter tops and serve.
Makes 40 rolls.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef in a little oil.
Mix tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper, chili powder and garlic salt together and pour over meat.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream; set aside. In a casserole dish, first spread noodles on bottom, next the meat mixture.
Cover with sour cream mixture.
Last, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until mixture is bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil and beat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Pour glaze over hot cake.

title: strawberry chiffon
directions: In a small saucepan, combine water, sugar and gelatin.
Cook over low heat until gelatin and sugar are dissolved, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in strawberries and chill for 1/2 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Use casserole dish for baking.
Cook noodles.
Layer 1 can of tuna in bottom.
Layer 1/2 can green peas, 1/2 can of soup and grated cheese over tuna.
Add crumbled Ritz crackers to top.
Do layers again.
Preheat oven to 350° and cook about 25 minutes.

title: pudding icing
directions: Note:
Especially good on dark chocolate cake.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute shrimp in fat in a large skillet for 5 minutes or until pink.
Remove from pan; add flour and brown lightly.
Add chopped seasonings and saute.
Add tomato sauce, water, thyme, bay leaf, sugar, garlic, salt and pepper.
Stir well and simmer in covered pan for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp and cook until tender.
Add parsley just before serving.
Serve over hot rice.

title: mamma's hay sticks
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter together, stirring constantly until melted.
Pour over noodles and marshmallows.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let sit for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruity pops
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water. Pour into plastic or paper cups, or pop molds.
Freeze until almost firm, about 2 hours.
Insert wooden sticks, or plastic spoons.
Freeze until firm.
Remove cups and sprinkle with multicolored sprinkles (optional).
Makes about 8 or 9 pops.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well; add jam and beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices; sift together alternately with milk.
Put a little flour on nuts and raisins; fold in cake batter. Bake at 350° in 3 or 4 pans.

title: mexican campfire dinner
directions: In a large, heavy kettle (over campfire), brown meat and onion; drain.
Add seasoning mix, tomatoes and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Mix the corn muffin mix as package directs.
Drop by spoonfuls on boiling mixture.
Cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: laura's french dressing
directions: Mix in blender and store in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, two at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and flavorings; beat well 2 minutes. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: oriental rice
directions: Saute pork, chicken, onion and mushrooms until lightly browned.
Stir in broth, salt, pepper and rice.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add water chestnuts, bean sprouts, celery, pimento and 2 tablespoons almonds.
Combine cornstarch, water, soy sauce and gravy.
Stir into pork and chicken.
Simmer two minutes or until thickened.
Garnish with remaining sliced almonds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour in ice cream freezer and freeze.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in coconut, Cool Whip and extract.
Pour in crust and freeze at least 1 hour.
Stand at room temperature to soften.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Toss beans, oil, vinegar, onion flakes, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Place in an ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and margarine.
Spoon over beans; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, bell pepper, pineapple, seasoned salt and 1 cup of nuts together.
Roll into remaining nuts and shape. Sometimes I use more than a cup of nuts to roll it in.
You can use your own judgement.
Refrigerate.
It's better if you make it a couple of days ahead of time.

title: hot crabmeat appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon mixture into 8-inch pie plate or small ovenware dish.
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot.
Serve with cold crisp pieces of raw vegetables.

title: grilled teriyaki
directions: Remove fat and outside membrane from meat.
Score both sides. Cut into 3 x 4-inch pieces diagonally across the grain.
Combine all ingredients and marinate steak in mixture 1 to 3 hours or more. Put on skewers and grill or broil 4 minutes on one side and 3 on the other.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar, milk and chocolate with the egg yolks together in a heavy pan. Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and butter, beating until thick and cool.
Will frost 2 layers.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Put in skillet and bring to a boil.
Put over chopped meat. Bake and serve.

title: apple crisp("an easy dessert")
directions: Put the apples in a buttered 10-inch pie tin.
Cut together the butter, flour and brown sugar.
Put on top of apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Boil, until sugar dissolves, first four ingredients.
Make dough of remaining ingredients.
Roll out in six portions.
Put apples on and sprinkle with a little additional sugar and cinnamon.
Pour cinnamon syrup over all.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: praline candy
directions: Combine pudding mix, evaporated milk, white sugar, brown sugar, and butter in sauce pan.
Stir and cook over low heat until sugar melts.
Add pecans and boil slowly until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water or reaches 234-238° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and beat for a few minutes.
Pour onto waxed paper by spoonfuls to cool.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake half of the batter for 15 minutes. Melt together and pour over baked cake the caramels, evaporated milk and oleo.
Over that, sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Spread remainder of the cake batter on top and bake 20 minutes at 350° until done.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Boil smoked sausage in water for 10 minutes to get fat out. Drain water.
In covered casserole (ovenproof) mix rice, oleo, bouillon, parsley, shallot, celery and water.
Add sausage and mix.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Stir.
Take cover off and bake 5 minutes more or until liquid is absorbed.

title: mint tea(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Boil tea bags and mint in water. Let it steep 15 minutes.
Add sugar, water and juice. Serve over ice. Garnish with lemon.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until very crisp.
Remove fat from pork and beans. Combine beans, brown sugar and molasses in 9-inch baking dish. Crumble bacon on top. Ready for oven.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Mix cooled chicken with grated cheese. Add sour cream to soup.
Mix and add chicken broth to thin with chilies.
Cover bottom of dish with a thin layer of soup mix. Place chicken and cheese on one side of tortilla; roll and place in dish.
Spread remaining sauce over tortillas; sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat roll-ups
directions: Pat out biscuit dough on floured surface into 1/2-inch thick rectangle.
Mix beef with eggs and seasonings; spread over dough. Roll as for jelly roll; cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place slices, cut side down, in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Spoon soup over each serving.

title: quick sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in.
Drop by teaspoonful two inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with greased bottom glass dipped in sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat with onion.	Drain.	Reserve small amount of meat. Pour in shell.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs and add cream and seasonings.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes more.
Top with reserved meat and cook 5 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Saute 1 chopped onion in 1 stick oleo.
Add 1 package frozen chopped broccoli.
Cook until tender.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 small jar Cheez Whiz.
Stir together and add 2 cups cooked rice.
Serve at once.

title: avocado sauce
directions: Mix the avocado
and egg yolk thoroughly.
Add the rest of the ingredients and season to taste.
Serve as a sauce with meat and poultry.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pea salad
directions: Grate boiled eggs into a bowl; add cheese, onion, and mayonnaise. Stir; add peas, salt, and pepper to taste.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Roll each piece of chicken in flour mixture until well coated.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, butter, eggs and raisins.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Combine brown sugar, nuts, flour, melted butter and spices.
Mix well and spread over casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: all's good pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, nuts, raisins and spices.
Beat egg whites.
Add last.
Bake slow until brown, approximately 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lazy daisy topping
directions: Mix all the ingredients and spread on baked cake.
Place 3-inches under broiler and broil until bubbly and brown (approximately 3 to 5 minutes).
It's especially good served warm.

title: apples and carrots
directions: In skillet, over medium-high heat, melt margarine.
Remove 1 tablespoon and toss with bread crumbs; set aside.
Add onions to margarine remaining in skillet; saute until tender.
In large bowl, toss onions with apples and next 5 ingredients until mixed. Pour into shallow baking dish; cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven 55 minutes.
Remove foil; sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake 15 minutes more or until apples are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: orange sherbet party punch
directions: Heat 2 cups water to boiling; add jello and sugar until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water and fruit juices.
Chill until ready to serve.
Spoon sherbet into punch bowl.
Pour over ginger ale.

title: gerald ham
directions: Mix both flavors in water and then put in bag with ham.
Cook until done.

title: abenaki summer squash soup
directions: Dice a squash but do not peel.
Saute in butter with seasonings.
Keep pan covered and do not allow to brown.
When soft, puree, then add the broth and simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: summer salad
directions: Chop all ingredients and cover with Italian dressing.
Let stand overnight.

title: greek salad
directions: Mix cheese, tomatoes, cucumbers and peppers.
Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt, garlic and onions together.
Combine with vegetables.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs and mix.
Add pineapple, cream and bread crumbs.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 40 minutes.

title: ford dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: island pan barbecue shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, except limes.
Marinate at room temperature for 1 hour.
Heat a dry skillet over medium-high heat. When skillet is hot, lay shrimp in pan.
Cook shrimp 2 to 4 minutes per side, depending on size.
Brush shrimp with remaining marinade before turning.
Serve with lime.

title: bread pudding
directions: In double boiler, add brown sugar and bread cubes.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Do not stir.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: quick rolls
directions: Add sugar and oil to buttermilk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine with buttermilk mixture.
Add flour.
Knead well. Roll out on floured board.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Put a pat of butter on each and fold over like an envelope.
Place in greased pan and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until it sets.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Mix well to remove lumps.
Gradually add milk, stirring until blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved 1/2 cup of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cut one large head of cabbage into fourths; cut out heart. Lightly butter both cut sides of each quarter and sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 slice of uncooked bacon on top of each quarter.
Wrap tightly in aluminum foil sprayed with Pam and place on medium grill for 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add celery, onions and green peppers to saute.
Reserve.
Boil 4 cups water with chicken soup mix.
(Half cup more if you like it sticky.)
Add Success rice (tear open envelopes and pour directly into water).
Boil until most of the soup has absorbed into rice.
Add sausage mixture and stir well, heating through.
May half recipe easily.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Dissolve bouillon in hot water and add to meat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes and green pepper.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Combine other ingredients into meat mixture.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Remove garlic.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat until smooth the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into graham crust. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: little pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add Velveeta until melted.
Add garlic powder, oregano and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir until mixed good.
Take a loaf of party rye bread (if you can't find party rye you can use regular rye bread and cut each slice of bread into 4 pieces).
Spread mixture on bread slices and put on cookie sheet. Put wax paper between each layer and freeze.
When frozen put in plastic bag and remove when ready to bake.	Put on cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes.
If you want them crisp, bake for 15 minutes.

title: grandma's old-fashioned nut loaf
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder 3 times; set aside.
Cream the butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add nuts and blend.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk a small amount at a time. Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and syrup; mix well.
Melt margarine and pour into mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 250° until firm and brown.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook 3 strips bacon in large pan.
When bacon is cooked, drain off fat.
Add 2 cups peeled and diced potatoes and diced onion. Cover with water and boil.
When potatoes and onion are cooked, add 4 cans of minced clams.
Continue cooking.
Add pinch of basil or thyme, 1/2 stick butter and milk.
Turn heat down when milk is added so you don't scorch the chowder.

title: stewed potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Add sliced potatoes, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to cover potatoes. Cook for 20 to 25 minutes.
When finished, add butter.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Soften butter and cheese.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and flour. Cream all together.
Make small balls; press thumb down in center. Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and then place icing in center.

title: sweet and sour ham
directions: Brown the ham in butter; add pineapple with syrup.
Cut peppers into strips and add to ham.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: marinated mixed vegetables(keeps 3 or 4 days, onion gets stronger)
directions: Four hours before serving, mix first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss gently to coat vegetables well. Cover and refrigerate, tossing occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese spread
directions: Soften cheeses; add salad dressing mix.
Mix with mixer.

title: banana sandwich bread
directions: Blend.
Put in greased bread pans (2).
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine in conventional manner.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, oil and eggs; beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.

Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely and spread Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting. Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup toasted coconut reserved from frosting recipe.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until thick.

title: turkey croquettes
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together milk, salt and pepper. Mix flour and water in shaker; shake well.
Add flour mixture to milk and add butter.
On medium-high heat, heat until becomes thickened.
Stir in turkey.

title: sour cream candied nuts
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix sugar, sour cream and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook, stirring to soft ball (236° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Add nuts and stir quickly to coat all sides.
Turn out on greased cookie sheets and separate nuts.
Makes about 1 1/8 pounds.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Stir together all ingredients, except Basic Baking Mix.
Mix well and add Basic Baking Mix.
Pour into 12 muffin cups (about 2/3 full).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with icing and raspberries (optional).

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until meat is well browned and onion is tender.
(Drain fat.)

title: marinated slaw
directions: Boil sugar, water, salt, mustard seed and vinegar for 3 minutes and cool.
Pour all ingredients over cabbage.
Let stand 12 hours and serve.
Keeps well in refrigerator for weeks.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients (except cocoa).
Mix cocoa with water and cook on low heat until thick.
Add shortening; mix well.
Cook until shortening melts and then cool for 5 minutes. Add dry ingredients, a little at a time; mix well after each addition.
Add coffee, eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Pound flour into them with a sharp knife or tenderizer.
Brown meat good.
Cover with onion, tomatoes, tomato sauce and salt and pepper.
Let simmer until tender.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain on paper towels and cut into small pieces. Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper, mixing well. Add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add broth; reduce to low heat and stir in cheese.
When cheese has melted, add broccoli and mix thoroughly.
You may also add cooked diced potatoes, carrots and green peas (about 1 cup each) for variety.

title: cherry squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to oleo in large mixing bowl, creaming at medium speed until light and fluffy.
At medium speed, add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
At low speed, add flour and lemon juice.
Pour batter into well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan . Mark off 24 squares.
Place 1 heaping tablespoonful pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix all together in plastic bag.
Shake in bag. Store in tight container.
Mix well. Looks oily at first; after it sets awhile, it will be dry and crisp.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine
flour
with
salt and pepper; pound into meat. Brown on
both
sides in shortening in 10 or 12-inch skillet. Add remaining
ingredients.
Simmer, covered, on top of range or bake at
for 1 1/2 or 2 hours.
Serve with vegetable gravy. Makes 6 servings.

title: mrs. marlin perkins' lemon charlotte
directions: Line a shallow serving bowl with split lady fingers.
Soften gelatin in orange juice.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Cool.
Fold in egg whites, then whipped cream.
Pour into bowl.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, spread with whipped cream and garnish with orange sections (mandarin).

title: hot dog heros
directions: Split hot dog lengthwise.
Insert cheese.
Separate biscuits. Flatten with palm.
Roll biscuits around hot dogs.
Place, seam side down, on a cookie sheet, about 1 inch apart.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Serve with mustard.
Makes enough for 20 kids.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, milk and salt in double boiler 3/4 hour.
Add butter before removing from stove.
Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Grease baking dish and set in pan of water.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: overnight breakfast quiche
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Spread bread evenly over bottom.
In medium skillet, brown sausage over medium heat.
Remove from heat and drain off fat.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs with electric mixer on low speed.
Stir in milk, then remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking. Preheat oven to 325° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until middle is set.
Makes 12 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine or butter.
Beat eggs and sugar; combine with first mixture.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder (sifted together 3 times) and add a little at a time.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup additional nuts over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch heavy aluminum pan.
Cut with table knife while still hot.
Place in metal fruit cake box, separate layers with wax paper and cover with lid immediately.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt bars and margarine.
Add pecans and cool.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add buttermilk. Add vanilla.
Mix with Milky Way bar mixture and bake in Bundt pan at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Can use 4 round pans for 8-inch cake.

title: beef stroganoff casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 13 x 9 baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Place beef in large skillet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Brown beef over medium-high heat until no longer pink, stirring to separate. Drain fat from skillet. Set beef aside. Heat oil in same skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add mushrooms, onion and garlic. Cook and stir 2 minutes or until onion is tender. Add wine. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in soup, sour cream and mustard until combined. Return beef to skillet. Place noodles in prepared dish. Pour beef mixture over noodles. Stir until noodles are well coated. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Add walnuts and mix.
Chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, chicken or turkey with onion, salt and pepper in skillet; drain.
Add tomato soup and green beans.
Stir together and place in casserole dish.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and run under cold water.
Chop together lettuce, pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Add vegetables to hamburger.
Smash Doritos and mix with vegetable mixture.
Pour Catalina dressing into mixture and mix.

title: biscuits on creamy chicken
directions: Rinse peas under warm water to separate.
Heat peas, chicken, soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper just to boiling in saucepan.
Keep warm while preparing biscuits.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Bring to a
good
boil.
I then add a little thickening of clear jell.
Bottle and seal.
Makes approximately 14 bottles.

title: i'm a little teapot tea
directions: In a large pitcher, combine the first five ingredients until dissolved.
Just before serving, stir in soda.
Yield:
2 quarts.

title: maes pound cake
directions: Cream crisco and butter together; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, baking powder, salt, flour, milk.
Mix well. No flavoring is needed, but you can use some if you would like. Bake at 275° for one hour and ten minutes.

title: spicy dark fruitcake
directions: Mix fruits, peels, raisins and nuts.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup over fruit mixture, mixing well.
Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with grape juice, beating until smooth after each addition.
Pour batter over fruits and mix well.
Line two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans with paper.
Bake in slow oven at 275° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until done.

title: hash brown and sausage casserole
directions: Spray an 8 x 12 casserole dish with nonstick spray. Place potatoes in bottom of pan. Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with sausage. In a saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese. Heat until cheese melts. Add sour cream. Pour over sausage and potatoes. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: hunter stew
directions: Dredge 1-inch cubes of beef in flour, pepper and salt.
Brown in a little fat in the bottom of a soup kettle.
Add onion and celery.
Cook for about 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix lightly.
Add enough water to cover entire mixture.
Cover tightly and cook about 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are cooked.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Bake at 300° for 18 to 22 minutes; heat thoroughly.
Serve with noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tomato basil squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Using lightly floured pastry roller, roll crust into a 12 x 15-inch rectangle. Place on cookie sheet or baking stone. Sprinkle crust with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Mix Parmesan, basil, mayonnaise, remaining Mozzarella and garlic. Thinly slice tomatoes over Mozzarella cheese. Spread cheese mixture over tomatoes evenly. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until top is golden and bubbly. Serve warm after cutting into squares.

title: snow punch
directions: Combine in punch bowl the juice, sugar, lemonade concentrate and water. Add ice cream. Stir until blended. Stir in ginger ale. Serve at once.

title: sherry trifle
directions: Line base of serving dish (clear, deep glass is nice) with cake or ladyfingers.
Drain raspberries, reserving the syrup. Moisten the cake with sherry and 2 to 3 tablespoons syrup from raspberries.
Spread raspberries over cake evenly.
(Cover and leave in refrigerator overnight if desired.)
Spread cooled vanilla pudding evenly over raspberries.
Top with layer of whipped cream.
Decorate with sprinkles, etc. as desired. Refrigerate until serving.
To serve, spoon onto dish, inserting spoon down through layers.

title: oatmeal cocoa chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine shortening, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and oatmeal. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a sprayed dish.
Mix together soups, sour cream and optional ingredients.
Pour on chicken.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs well.
Add sugar, oil, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla, beating until thoroughly blended.
Fold in zucchini and walnuts.
Turn into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until done. Cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 loaves or 1 Bundt pan bread.

title: tahitian delight
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directions say to.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan and let cool when done.
Blend cream cheese, pudding mix and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip topping.
Spread pineapple over cake.
Spread cream cheese mixture over pineapple.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill.

title: zoie's flat syrup cake
directions: Mix egg, butter, salt, milk, soda, flour, vanilla, sugar and syrup.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together except bread crumbs.
Put in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: To sauteed onion add celery, beef, salt and pepper.
Cook until just a little brown.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and confectioners sugar together; spread on bottom and sides of baked pie crust.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; stir in water and 1 cup berries.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and clear; reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cool 5 minutes.
Arrange remaining berries in pie crust.
Pour cooled glaze over strawberries.
Just before serving, garnish with whipped cream.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise into halves.
Slip out yolks; mash them with a fork.
Mix in salt, mustard, pepper and mayonnaise. Fill egg whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it lightly.
(You may add chopped pickles or chopped olives to yolk mixture.) Arrange eggs on serving plate.
Cover and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.
Serves 6.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Add soup, broth and rice. Bake in oven for 45 minutes (until rice is done) at 375°.

title: chef bogle's lasagne
directions: Chop onions, green pepper and garlic very fine.
Saute in olive oil on low flame in deep pot for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle meat tenderizer evenly on chopped meat.
Add one egg and 1 tablespoon of Accent.
Mix thoroughly, then place in same pot with onions, green pepper and garlic.
Cook for 15 minutes over medium flame. While still cooking, add the 2 cans of tomato paste and 2 cans mushrooms; pour water off first.
Blend together and add 3 pinches of oregano.
Simmer over low flame until all ingredients have mixed well.
Season to taste.
Do not add salt.
Drain off excessive grease and place on a very low flame.

title: bacon wieners
directions: Cook bacon slightly in microwave. Wrap around wiener.
Mix plum jelly, brown sugar and Karo syrup. Pour over wieners and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix in large bowl; form into 2 rolls.
Place in foil (bright side out).
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove foil.
Bake for 3 to 4 hours at 200°.
Cool.
Store in foil in refrigerator or freezer.

title: nacho "pizza" dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with 2 packages of softened cream cheese. Spread evenly on large, round platter.
Top with salsa.
Sprinkle with lettuce, then cheese and tomato.
Garnish with olives.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan the graham cracker crumbs and oleo.
Chill.
Beat confectioners sugar, eggs, oleo and vanilla for 20 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Drain pineapple and spread on top.
Cut in thirds lengthwise the bananas.
Layer banana over pineapple.
Spread on top the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Chill several hours.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix with a fork until crumbly. Add enough water to make a firm dough.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Take chicken off the bone.
Mix soups, green chilies and chicken broth.
Heat.
Place layer of tortillas in greased 9
x 13 x 3-inch pan.
Place layer of chicken over the pieces of tortillas.
Sprinkle with green onions, salt and pepper.
Pour half of soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar; bring to boil and boil 3 minutes. Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; stir until mixture is thoroughly mixed.
Cool.
Add apples, nuts, celery and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: chocolate peanut chunks
directions: Melt chips and oil over boiling water.
Remove from heat and add raisins and peanuts, stirring until raisins and peanuts are well coated.
Drop in bite size clusters onto a greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: corn crisp chicken
directions: Roll chicken pieces in milk then in cornflakes.
Place in foil covered baking dish.
Lightly cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bev's chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Place in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Put chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: divinity
directions: Mix syrup, water, sugar and salt.
Cook until mixture forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Pour 1/2 mixture in beaten egg whites, beating all the time.
Let that mix a few seconds and then add remaining.
Beat until starts to thicken.
Add nuts and drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: pizza crust
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix dry yeast into warm water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Mix in flour and oil and knead for 5 minutes.
Roll out on floured or oiled surface, then place in pizza pan.
Add your favorite filling.
Bake for 15 minutes or until done.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown seasoned chops in skillet; slice tomatoes and onions. Layer with chops.
Cover; bake 1 hour at 350°.
Reduce the pan liquid and serve with rice.

title: tapioca fruit salad
directions: Take
the juice from the pineapple and mandarin oranges and add
water	to
equal
cups.
Add Tang and the tapioca pudding; mix
well.
Cook
on
the	stove until it comes to a full	boil and thicken, mixing constantly.
Remove from heat, add
Knox gelatine and stir quickly.	Cool slightly, add fruit and chill.

title: coating for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well, coat skinned chicken, fish or seafood and bake, makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Cover with rest of Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: turtle (land variety)
directions: Drop turtles into boiling water.
Boil 1 hour.
Remove from pot and take skin off of legs and feet.
In fresh boiling water, cook 1 1/2 hours.
Once the turtles cool, clean thoroughly.
Cut into pieces.
Add vegetables to make stew.

title: stayabed stew(this is for those days when you're out all day.)
directions: Mix these things up in a 3-quart casserole dish that has a tight lid.
Put the lid on and put the casserole in 275° oven.
It will cook all day by itself and be done in five hours.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Combine chicken, soy sauce and salt.
Marinate 15 minutes. Lightly brown rice in oil in large skillet over medium heat; stir frequently.
Add chicken with soy sauce and broth.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in onion, green pepper, celery and cabbage; cook until vegetables are tender and liquid is absorbed. Push mixture to sides of pan.
Add eggs; cook until almost set. Blend into rice mixture.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add Karo syrup, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt. Mix until well blended, then stir in pecan halves. Pour into pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 65 minutes or until a knife inserted into pie comes out clean. Double recipe for 2 pies.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal and flour.
Whisk eggs.
Add all other ingredients to cornmeal mixture and mix until wet.
Pour into a greased cast-iron skillet; bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all and heat just to melt cheese.
Serve with firm potato chips.

title: cool gazpacho
directions: Combine all
ingredients in a large container and chill at least 2 hours.
Serves 20 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: kosher dill vinegar
directions: Boil salt, vinegar and water and pour over packed jar.
Seal tightly.

title: miniature drop biscuits
directions: In bowl with pastry blender, cut the butter into the flour until particles are invisible.
Add sour cream; with a fork, stir just until flour is moist.
Drop into miniature muffin tins and bake at 425° until brown.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add milk, butter, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a baking dish and cover with mixture of remaining white sugar, brown sugar, cocoa and water.
Cake will be on top and pudding in bottom after baking 1 hour in moderate oven. Serve with whipped cream.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook on stove the green beans until juice is cooked down.
Add cream of mushroom soup and drained mushrooms.
Remove from heat and stir.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add French fried onions on top.
Bake at 325° until onions are golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and crushed pineapple with juice and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add chopped walnuts last.
Mix well and divide into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: brisket sauce
directions: Combine chili sauce with Coke.
Mix well.
Pour over brisket and bake at 325° for 4 to 5
hours.
Makes a very tender brisket.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and red onion into small pieces.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Serve chilled.

title: old bay baked chicken breast(low-fat recipe)
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam or use broiler pan.
Wash chicken breasts and skin.
Sprinkle Old Bay on both sides good. Put in dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° or 400° until done.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Combine all ingredients. Grease a crock-pot with 2 tablespoons vegetable oil and add the mixture.
Cut thin slices of cheese and put on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low heat.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix in saucepan until oleo is melted.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Add pecans.
Fold in ice cream. In a 13 x 9-inch pan, place 18 gingersnaps on bottom.
Spread half of the mixture over the gingersnaps.
Then spread 18 more gingersnaps over that.
Place the remaining mixture over all. Freeze 5 hours and top with Cool Whip.

title: orange salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin.
Add marshmallows; stir until dissolved.
Defrost orange juice; stir in sugar.
Add gelatin, cream cheese, and pineapple to mixture.
Add bananas and orange sections; stir until well mixed.
Fold in whipping cream which has been whipped.
Pour into large container and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Yields 8.

title: macaroni cheese salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard and salt; add.
Toss lightly and chill.
Serve on greens (lettuce).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini thin.
Boil with salt and water for 5 minutes. In a saucepan combine chicken soup (undiluted), onions, carrots and sour cream.
Cook a few minutes until hot.
Mix oleo and stuffing mix, then put 1/2 of it between layers of zucchini and the rest on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, chives and pimento.
Mix well.

title: old fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Simmer chicken slowly, until tender, in salted water to cover. Cut margarine into flour and eggs; mix well.
Roll thin as for pastry.
Cut in narrow strips.
Drop into boiling water with chicken and cook for 10 minutes or until done.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: big mama's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and 2 cups sugar thoroughly. Add eggs one at a time, beating until real fluffy. Add the other cup of sugar. Beat until sugar is dissolved. Put soda in buttermilk. Sift flour and salt together 3 times. Alternate adding flour and milk, beginning and ending with flour. Add mace and lemon flavoring. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a greased and floured pan. Freezes really well. Sometimes I just cut off slices and put back in freezer. Can do ahead.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Put all the ingredients in blender, except bread. Pour mixture over bread. Brown 1 pound sausage; drain on paper towel and pour over mixture. Add 1 cup grated cheese. Cover and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours. Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in a small amount of salted water until tender; drain. Add cracker crumbs (reserving 1/4 cup for top), cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and 3 tablespoons margarine. Spoon into a greased casserole dish (2-quart). Top with remaining cracker crumbs and margarine. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown. Yields about 8 servings.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix all together.
Spread 1/4 to 1/3 cup of mixture all over tortilla.
Roll up in plastic wrap and chill a few hours.
Slice about 1/2 inch thick, eat the ends.
Serve with Picante Sauce.

title: chocolate creamy fudge
directions: Mix and stir first 3 ingredients.
Cook and boil 5 minutes or until soft ball stage.
Then add chocolate bits and vanilla.
Cook only until bits are melted.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Stir until mixed well, then pour into greased pan.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix egg white and water.
Add pecans and stir until coated well with egg white.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until coated well.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: chocolate, chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mix together the cake and pudding mixes, sour cream, oil, eggs and water. Do not Beat. Stir in chocolate chips. Pour batter into a well-greased nonstick 12-cup

Bundt pan. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until top is springy to the touch. Do not overbake. Cool in pan about 45 minutes. Invert cake onto cake plate. Serve plain, sprinkled with confectioners sugar or drizzle favorite icing.

title: quick and easy nutty cheese bar
directions: Stir together in a medium bowl dry cake mix, oleo and 3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Press evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, 3/4 cup nuts and cream cheese.
Spread evenly over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin fruit bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease (not oil) bottom of two 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, combine pumpkin, sugar, butter, water and eggs.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes; remove and cool completely.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars, vanilla and peanut butter until smooth.
Add oatmeal, baking powder, chocolate chips and M&M's candy.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cookies can be frozen.
Makes 15 dozen.

title: fresh green salsa
directions: Cook chilies together until soft.
Mix together onion, garlic and salt. Add cooked chilies and tomatoes. Blend well.
If too thick or hot, add more water.

title: chinese fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter in a glass mixing bowl in the microwave for 2 minutes. Sir well to blend. Add marshmallows and chow mein noodles. Stir well. Pour into lightly greased 8 inch square pan. Chill for 1 1/2 hours.

title: party snacks
directions: Beat softened cream cheese and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip. Slice cookies into halves.
Spread with filling.
Put top of cookie on filling.

title: seaweed's cake
directions: Top with remaining batter and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: country style chicken
directions: Cut broiler into individual servings.
Salt and pepper, if desired.
Then dredge in flour mixed with paprika.
Brown in hot chicken fat melted in skillet.
Add onion and about 1 cup water. Put cover on skillet and cook slowly, until chicken is done. Serve with Cream Gravy.

title: cheese and apple spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add cheese and apples; mix well. Chill. Serve with apple wedges, crackers and bread.
Yield:
1 2/3 cups.

title: turkey and pickle roll-ups
directions: Let cream cheese sit out until room temperature.
Drain pickles.
Spread softened cream cheese on a slice of turkey. Place pickle on the end and roll up.
Let roll-ups refrigerate for at least 1 hour before slicing into 1 inch slices.
You may also use Ham for this recipe.

title: quick minestrone
directions: Place undrained kidney beans in large pot.
Mash 2/3 of the beans and leave the rest whole.
Add salt, garlic salt, garlic pepper, oil and parsley.
Stir well.
Add all vegetables, butter, tomato sauce and water; simmer 1 hour or more.
Add sherry and macaroni; simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Serves 6.

title: hashed brown potatoes
directions: Grate potatoes coarsely; toss in onion, salt and pepper.
In 10-inch skillet, over high heat, heat butter with bacon fat; add potatoes.
Press firmly with turner; shape into circle, leaving 1/2 inch trough around edges.
After 12 to 15 minutes, lift potatoes to see if brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat in skillet heated to medium hot.
After about 5 minutes, add the chopped onion, celery and green pepper, stirring mixture occasionally until red color is out of the meat and vegetables are slightly soft.
Add all remaining ingredients. Reduce heat so mixture only simmers gently.
Cook uncovered for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: joann's whatchacallit pie
directions: Use a round pie pan, glass if possible.
Dip cookies in milk; lay in bottom of pan.
Spread Cool Whip, then sprinkle with coconut.
Repeat layers with cookies dipped in milk, Cool Whip and coconut.
Decorate with pecans, if desired and top with cherries.

title: easter bread
directions: Melt margarine or butter in milk.
Add sugar, just until warm. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat eggs until light in color, about 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients, then add enough flour to handle dough.
Put on bread board and knead the dough.
Dough will be sticky.
Oil big pot and top of dough.
Cover with Saran Wrap, towel and blanket.
Let rise double the size.
Punch down and knead about 5 minutes.
Then put into pans.
Let rise 1 hour.
Beat egg and brush on top of bread.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pepper kokar(swedish cookie)
directions: Heat sugar, syrup, shortening and spices to almost boil.
Add soda and cool.
Add eggs, baking powder and flour.
Mix and roll thin.
Sprinkle sugar.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: green bean soup
directions: Cut carrots in thin slices.
Put in 4-quart pot 3/4 full of water.
Add salt and cook 10 minutes.
Cut bacon in small pieces and brown.
Add enough flour to make a paste and brown well.
Add paprika.
Add the beans, juice and all, potatoes and bacon thickening to carrots.
Cook about 15 minutes until carrots and potatoes are done and soup is thickened.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients into a covered container.
For each serving, place 2 to 3 teaspoons mix in each cup.
Fill with apple cider, apple juice, cranberry juice or water; stir.

title: left-ovah goulosh
directions: Grab a large kettle, 'n dump a turkey carcass (skin, giblets, leftover gravy, etc.) in it.
Add watah, 1 teaspoon salt, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Brang to a boil.
Reduce heat, covah 'n simmer fur 'bout 1 1/2 hours or 'til you have made a rich stock. Strain 'n return to pot.
Pick all the meat off 'n add to this (you gotta have sum meat!) the remaining ingredients.
Kiver agin 'n simmer fur anothah 1 1/2 hours.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer each one as listed. Seal with salad dressing and sprinkle sugar on top.
Let set overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to mixture.
Place flour in large bowl and add dates, orange slice candy and nuts.
Stir to coat.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture and mix by hand.
Bake in greased tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: zippy oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pancake mix, onion, salt and garlic powder in a paper bag.
Shake chicken pieces lightly in bag until well coated.
Place skin side up on rack in large shallow baking pan.
Dot with margarine.
Bake for 1 hour for a 2 1/2 to 3 pound chicken.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Add 1/4 cup sugar while cooking.
Let cool.
Add pineapple.
Fold Cool Whip or whipped cream into rice and pineapple.
Keep in refrigerator.
This can be used instead of dessert.

title: bootlegger beans
directions: Fry bacon in iron skillet.
Brown onion in bacon grease. Crumble bacon and add all ingredients in skillet, keeping grease. Bring to a boil and simmer until thick.

title: goldie lock's brownies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cut into serving pieces when cooled.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish in oven; remove.
In large bowl, beat eggs; add flour, milk and seasonings.
Add cheese, spinach and onion.
Pour into dish and bake 35 minutes. Cool 45 minutes and cut into bite size pieces.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix flour, egg, pudding mix, milk and butter.
The mixture will be a little doughy.
Spread into pie shell.
Drain peaches. Save juice.
Spread peaches over crust.
Mix cream cheese (softened), sugar and 3 tablespoons peach juice together.
Spread over peaches.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except meat, and let stand until soft.
Mix in meat.
Shape into 1-inch balls and arrange on baking sheet.
Broil meatballs until well browned, about 5 to 8 minutes. Makes 35 to 40 meatballs.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in 1-quart saucepan to soften. Place over low heat, stirring until gelatin is dissolved, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in salt and lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature.

title: grandma's carrot cake
directions: Boil carrots, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, sugar, salt and shortening for 20 minutes.
Then add eggs, soda and water; mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into fruit cake pan or deep pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake springs back.
Wait 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: hatcher crackers
directions: Place crackers neatly on SilverStone (nonstick) cookie sheet. Crackers must fit tightly so cheese will not run between the crackers.
Sprinkle crackers with red pepper to taste.
Spread grated cheese on each cracker.
Turn on broiler.
Place pan on bottom rack and leave door open.
When the cheese begins to dry out and most of the bubbles are firm on top, remove the pan from the oven.
Allow the oven to cool.
Return the cookie sheet to the oven set at 150° and close the oven door.
Leave the crackers several hours (at least) to dry out.
Crackers are best left in the oven until ready to serve (even for days).

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Put chicken, broccoli, mushrooms and margarine in a large frying pan and cook until done.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Mix stuffing and chicken mixture together in a casserole dish.
Add gravy to moisten.
Serves 4.

title: gaines pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and margarine until well blended.
Add eggs (1 at a time).
Add sifted flour and baking powder slowly with milk.
Mix well.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes.
Begin with cold oven.

title: korean barbecue beef (boul-koh-kee)
directions: Add water and sugar to beef and mix very gently by hand. Combine remaining ingredients and again mix gently with the beef. Barbecue on a grill, broil, or sizzle in a hot pre-heated ungreased skillet.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, adding pecans last.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce the heat to 350°.
Bake until done or silver knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine 1 package of beef Rice-A-Roni with 1 pound ground beef and beaten egg.
Shape into small meatballs (approximately 20). Brown on all sides in skillet.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes. Scoop potatoes out of shell, being careful to keep shells intact. Mix potatoes with enough milk to make smooth consistency. Add butter, salt, pepper, sugar, sour cream, chopped green onions, grated cheese and bacon (crisp and crumbled).

title: working girl's coconut cake
directions: This cake is best made a few days before serving.
Bake cake combining cake mix, pudding,
mayonnaise,
oil,
eggs and water; mix well and bake at 350°.
When cake is cool, cut into 2 or 3 layers or use layer pans to bake 2 or 3 layers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Prepare spinach as directed on package.
Combine cheese, soup and milk.
Heat until cheese is creamy.
Layer spinach, soup mixture and half of onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and place on top the remainder of the onions.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form ball and chill before serving.

title: carrot sandwiches
directions: Mix and refrigerate 12 hours.
I make ribbon sandwiches. These are delicious and it can be frozen and used a couple days later.
Great for a wedding reception.

title: quick cabbage rolls
directions: Chop cabbage; spread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown meat and onion in large skillet; stir in rice, pepper and salt.
Spoon mixture over cabbage.
In small pan heat tomato soup and water until hot.
Pour over all ingredients.
Sprinkle with grated cheese (Cheddar).
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: a delicious punch
directions: Mix the juices and 7-Up together and add the ice cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place all ingredients in a glass dish.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until well blended.
Spread in a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine fruits and juice.
Chill.
Arrange fruits in lettuce cups.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Garnish with cherry.
Serve with whipped cream fruit salad dressing.
Makes six servings.

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: Heat 1/3 cup olive oil in large skillet or wok.
Add eggplant and saute until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Add 2 teaspoons olive oil to skillet.
Add onions, celery and garlic; saute about 5 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Blend in soup, cream cheese and milk; add seafood and corn.
Bring to boil; simmer about 10 minutes.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in water.
Mix remaining ingredients well and press into Pyrex dish or sheet cake pan lined with foil. Chill and slice.

title: sweet and creamy corn
directions: Blend all dry ingredients; set aside. Heat corn, butter and half and half until butter is melted. Add in dry ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes. May need to add extra flour to thicken.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together sugar and butter until fluffy.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, pecans and cherries.
Form dough into 3 seven-inch rolls.
Roll in flaked coconut
to
coat
the
outside.
Wrap dough in waxed paper or clear plastic wrap.
Chill thoroughly.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Cream
shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs.
Add the sifted
dry ingredients.
Chill dough in refrigerator for awhile. Shape dough into walnut size balls.
Roll top of each ball in
a mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon.	Bake on ungreased cookie
sheet
at
for 8 to 10 minutes.
Young children love to make these.

title: cheese pecan ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, steak sauce, nuts, garlic and hot pepper sauce.
Form ball.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill.

title: flat branch raisin bars
directions: Cook the raisins in the water.
Remove from heat; stir in the soda.
While the raisins are cooking, mix the remaining ingredients as directed.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour; stir in raisins, water and nuts.
Spread into a well-greased cookie sheet with sides (jelly roll pan). Batter will be thin, but will rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing.
Cut into bars.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon
milk and sugar in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on pie crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in pumpkin pie mix and spices with wire whisk; mix well. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish as desired.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender. Drain.
Brown beef with onion and celery.
Layer ingredients in a buttered casserole.
Cover with 1/4 cup finely chopped Cheddar cheese. Cover casserole and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Melt shortening and add sugar.
Cool slightly and add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when almost cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Alternate layers of potatoes and flour mix in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with pepper; dot with butter and pour on milk just to top layer of potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, covered; then uncover and bake at 350° until done.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, onion, green pepper, seasoned salt and 1 cup pecans in a bowl.
Mix well. Shape into a ball. Roll in remaining pecans to coat.
Wrap in waxed paper and store in refrigerator.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: veal scaloppine casserole
directions: Chop onions and saute in skillet using 3 tablespoons butter. Remove onions to 1 1/2-quart casserole. Dust slices of veal in seasoned flour and brown in skillet, using 1/3 to 1/2 cup butter. When browned, place veal in casserole.
Add crushed garlic, rosemary and consomme.
Pour over veal.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix with melted margarine and pour on top of chicken and rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine juice, beaten eggs, sugar and flour.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add jello and mix well. When cool, pour over fruit that has been prepared in a large bowl. Chill.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and put into greased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: peanut butter cornflakes
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until blended.
Stir in cornflakes.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in the milk.
Mix together corn, eggs, flour and milk.
Add pimentos.
Put in greased baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: danish ebel-skiver
directions: Beat egg yolks until light. Add oil, sugar and buttermilk. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to buttermilk mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture. Bake in greased hot ebel-skiver pan. Turn gradually until done inside. Serve with syrup or brown sugar.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Saute onions, pepper and oleo.
Mix sauteed mixture with chicken, cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Roll biscuits as thin as you want and spread chicken mixture on each one.
Roll up to put seam down on pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Slice hot dogs and mix beans, syrup, brown sugar, onion, ketchup and mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Place the sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in a pan and cook for 2 minutes.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Pour cocoa mixture over mixture in bowl and mix well.
Drop on wax paper or buttered pan.
Let cool and serve.

title: alex's texas beans
directions: In huge pot, presoak beans as directed on package.
Bring beans and lentils to a boil over medium heat.
