Combine all other ingredients except 1/2 of bacon.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add remaining bacon and simmer 1 1/2 hours on medium-low heat.
Serve with flour tortilla or French bread.
Serves 1 Fellowship.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into graham cracker crust and chill several hours before serving.

title: crab puffs
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil; drain. Combine with crabmeat, white sauce, eggs, seasonings and cracker meal.
Fry in deep hot shortening at 375° until brown.

title: southern green beans(serves 4)
directions: Mix brown sugar, vinegar, bacon drippings and salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange green beans and onion in casserole.
Pour mixture over them.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cook 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, garlic powder and oregano (to taste).
Add soup and macaroni; mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place sliced cheese on top, enough to cover complete pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt together.
Beat egg yolks and add with milk.
Cook until thick on medium heat.
Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour in a baked pie shell. Add meringue and sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: grandma nine's blueberry muffins
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add the yolks of eggs, milk, flour, spices, baking powder and salt.
Beat the egg whites to a stiff froth.
Fold in gently.
Add berries and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Use graham crackers and 1 stick melted butter for crust. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish (I use a pie dish).

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain on paper towels.
Return to pan; add onions and peppers.
Cook until soft.
Add beans and tomatoes; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour bean mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat egg in small bowl; add milk and cornbread mix.
Stir until smooth.
Spoon cornbread batter over bean mixture and smooth.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove and sprinkle with cheese.
Cook 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted and sides are slightly brown. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: lost bread
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Soak bread in mixture as you prepare pan.
In frying pan heat oil on high heat.
Place bread in frying pan and cook on both sides until brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: inside-outside ravioli
directions: Mix bread crumbs, oil, American cheese and spinach in a bowl. Mix well, then add shells.
Put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased casserole dish.
Mix cooked hamburg with sauce and pour over mixture of shells.
Spread Mozzarella cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; peel onions and cut 1/4-inch thick.
Put in layers.
Sprinkle salt on each layer. Let stand for 2 to 3 hours. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Add cucumbers and onions; simmer for 10 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Mix and heat first 5 ingredients.
Add cheese, butter and broccoli.
Take 2 cups of the milk and add 1/2 cup flour and mix well.
Add to other 2 cups milk and pour into first mixture.
Cook until it thickens.
Makes 2 quarts.
Can be frozen.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Pour into crust.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg together.
Stir in rhubarb.
Let stand while preparing pie crust, then stir the above well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
If desired, serve with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple together in a pan; let come to a boil.
Cool, then add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Stir well.
Fold in apricots.
Refrigerate to set.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots just until tender.
Drain, reserving water. Saute onion in butter.
Combine carrots and onion with remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted butter in pan.
Beat together sugar, eggs and 2 sticks margarine.
Slice bananas on crust; put mixture on bananas.
Add pineapples.
Add Cool Whip.
Top with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: butter-crumb corn patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup bread crumbs. Shape into patties using 1/4 cup of the mixture for each. Sprinkle both sides of patties with reserved crumbs.
Quick-freeze on cookie sheet.
Wrap for freeze storage.
To serve, fry frozen patties in butter until golden brown, turning once.
Serve hot. Makes 10 to 12 patties.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in a greased Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: crab and shrimp salad
directions: Have bread frozen.
Cut crusts from loaf.
Butter one side of each slice.
Cut into small cubes.
Mix together with the onion. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, add the eggs, shrimp, crabmeat, Miracle Whip and mayonnaise.
Toss ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and allow to stand for 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Fresh seafood or chicken also makes good salad. Serves 12.

title: indian pudding
directions: Gradually add corn meal to hot milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and slightly thickened.
Add molasses. Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt, then add cold milk and mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased pudding dish.
Bake in slow oven at 275° to 300° for 2 hours.
Serve hot with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: oven-fried yellow squash
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper. Set aside. Combine egg and water; beat well. Dip squash in egg mixture; dredge in cornmeal mixture. Lightly coat a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with cooking spray. Place squash slices in a single layer in a pan. Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown, turning once. Yield: 6 servings.

title: idiot's delight
directions: Peel, cut up and boil eggplant.
If you're going to use hot pork sausage, you needn't put salt in the water.

title: basic meat balls
directions: Place ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion and salt in bowl. Add specified ingredients to prepare either Italian, Oriental or Scandinavian meatballs. follow remaining procedures as directed in desired recipe.

title: slim jim chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in a 5-quart pan; drain all excess fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 1 to 2 hours.
Stir. Remove bay leaf.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings; 156 calories per serving.

title: baked noodles casserole
directions: Cook noodles separately.
Brown beef.
Put chopped celery, onions and peppers in pan with beef.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients with tomatoes and tomato soup. Mix with cooked noodles.
Season and add grated cheese on top. Bake slowly 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat the eggs until frothy.
Stir in the remaining ingredients until well blended.
Turn into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and pour over salad.
Place in refrigerator and leave overnight!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Mix mushroom soup, mayonnaise and egg together.
Combine with broccoli and 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: granny's seashells
directions: Prepare seashells as instructed on package.
When seashells are cooked, drain.
Add soup and cheese.
Stir until mixture is creamy.
Serve and enjoy.

title: flourless peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll into small balls.
Bake for about 10 minutes on a greased cookie sheet at 350°.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Store in airtight container.
To serve: place 4 level tsp. in cup.
Add boiling water.
Stir Well.
Yield: about 33 servings.
Makes great gifts by placing in small containers.

title: perfect biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Measure dry ingredients into a bowl and stir thoroughly.
Cut shortening into flour mixture with a pastry blender until mixture looks like "meal".
Make a well in the dry ingredients and add milk.
Stir with a fork until mixture rounds up in a ball and no dry ingredients remain.
Avoid overhandling.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix and pour into baked pie crust or graham cracker crust. Chill.
Top with whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: plott's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls. Heat butter in
frying
pan.
Fry
them
and keep turning them over until they are brown.
Heat is about medium.
Makes 40 to 50 meatballs or 4 pans full.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with butter.
Add layer of cracker crumbs, layer of drained asparagus, layer of cheese and repeat until all ingredients are used.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: madrisciana (italian tomato sauce with bacon)
directions: In a large skillet, saute blended olive oil with green pepper and onions.
Add garlic; heat until golden brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, basil and parsley.
Stir and simmer, uncovered, for approximately 1 hour.
Add crumbled bacon to finished sauce just before serving.
Serves 5 to 6 adults as main course.

title: peachy yams
directions: Drain peach halves.
Arrange halves with cut side up in baking dish.
(To make peaches stand upright, cut thin slice from bottom of each half.)
Cream the butter and mashed yams.
Add brown sugar, orange peel and salt.
Add brandy and blend.
Spoon mixture onto peach halves.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. (Can microwave on High for 4 minutes, turning once during cooking.)
Serves 8.

title: black forest cheesecake
directions: Spread cookie crumbs on bottom of spring-form pan coated with cooking spray.
Beat the cream cheese until fluffy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Gradually add egg substitute, mixing well. Add melted chocolate, cocoa and vanilla, mixing until blended. Stir in sour cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; run a knife around edge of pan.
Cool on wire rack; cover and chill for at least 8 hours.
Top each slice with cherries and cream.

title: tuna deviled eggs
directions: Hard-cook eggs.
Remove shells.
Cut each egg in half and remove yolks.
Mash yolks with a fork and add tuna.
Mix well. Add salt and pepper, if needed.
Pile yolk mixture into egg whites.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain. Add rest of the ingredients; cook for a few minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime dissolved in water for 24 hours.
Rinse well and soak in clear water for 4 hours or overnight.
Combine vinegar, 2 cups water, salt and spices.
Then soak cucumbers in cold vinegar solution for 4 hours or overnight.
Boil 40 minutes. Pack in jars and seal.

title: mom's dumplings
directions: Mix egg and flour to a sticky consistency. Drop by spoonful into boiling chicken broth.
Let boil for about 10 minutes. Serves about 4.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Add flour and 7-Up; add flavor.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: provincial rabbit
directions: Dice all veggies.
Brown rabbits in large skillet in small amount of oil.
Remove; add all veggies.
Cook until tender. Place rabbits on top.
Add wine; simmer rapidly until done. Serves 8 to 10.

title: snow cream
directions: Add sugar, vanilla and milk to snow in bowl.
Mix with spoon and serve at once.

title: venison ribs with mushroom sauce
directions: Heat grease on medium heat in large iron skillet.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat ribs.
Brown ribs on both sides.
Add onions.
Mix soup with water; smooth out mix.
Now add to ribs. Add mushrooms.
Simmer until tender, about 1 hour.

title: creamy chocolate heath balls
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt chocolate bars (or chocolate chips) over low heat, stirring often.
Cool to room temperature. Fold in Cool Whip and Heath Bits 'O Brickle (mixture will thicken).
Cover and chill at least one hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in crushed pecans.
Chill thoroughly.

title: lucille's dill pickles
directions: Place onto each canning jar 1 large garlic clove and 1 piece of dill.
Bring 2 quarts of water to boil.
Add salt and vinegar, bringing back to a boil.
Cover cucumbers with boiling solution and seal.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup of the flour, the sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add mashed banana, shortening and milk.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until blended, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining flour; beat until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes on a wire rack.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly on a wire rack.

title: chili corn bread
directions: Prepare muffin mix according to package directions; stir in melted butter, corn, chilies and 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Use remaining butter to grease 9-inch pie pan; pour in batter. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup cheese over batter.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle of bread comes out clean.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and spices.
Mix soda with milk and add with flour.
Add jam, raisins and nuts.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; mix well.
Cut in shortening. Combine milk and egg.
Add to flour; stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll dough to 1-inch thickness.
Cut and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Yields 15 biscuits.

title: linguine florentine
directions: Remove and discard stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly. Place spinach in a large Dutch oven (do not add water); cover and cook over medium heat about 4 minutes or until wilted. Drain spinach well and squeeze between paper towels until barely moist. Finely chop spinach; set aside.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Preheat waffle maker. Put all ingredients (except egg white) in a large bowl; beat on low speed until moistened. Then increase speed to medium; beat until smooth. By hand, gently fold in beaten egg whites. Pour batter by 1/2 cup. Close lid and bake.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast, skin and bone.
Cut into chunks.
Cook broccoli until crisp-tender; drain.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place chicken chunks on top of the broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and spread over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: Pour into punch bowl and decorate with fresh fruit.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Mix the sugar and 4 cups water and boil for 5 minutes; let cool. Bring the coffee and 1/4 cup water to a boil. Then add this coffee mixture to the cooled sugar/water. Using empty dark glass gallon jug, add the vodka and vanilla beans. Put these in jug, then add the above mixture. Shake well. Put in paper bag and put in dark cool place for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: mrs. wintle's lemon curd tarts(makes 4 dozen miniature tarts.)
directions: Combine lemon rind, lemon juice and sugar in top of double boiler.
Add butter.
Heat over boiling water, stirring until butter is melted.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly until the mixture is thick enough to pile slightly (about 15 minutes).
Spoon filling into cooled tarts.

title: italian medallions
directions: Amounts of ingredients depend on number being served.
Chop onions or shallots and garlic, cut sausages into bite size pieces. Flatten veal and chicken.
Saute all in olive oil and butter until golden on a medium to low heat.
Add fresh mushrooms; stir. Add Marsala wine to the above; saute for a few minutes.
Serve over hot cooked fettuccine.
Top with fresh grated Romano cheese. Serve with greens and garlic bread.
This dish is easy and elegant.
The Marsala wine amount should be enough to coat the fettuccine and the meats.

title: beef enchilada casserole(lighter eating - 5.5 points)
directions: To prepare sauce, in medium saucepan, stir 1/4 c. of chili sauce and the flour until flour is dissolved. Gradually stir in remaining chili sauce, tomato puree and chili powder. Bring mixture to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally; cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes, until slightly thickened. Remove from heat; let cool.

title: aunt shelley's gingersnaps
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add 2 cups flour (approximate).
Roll to thin 1/8 to 1/16-inch.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: egg puff brunch
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Press down in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: minute steaks with gravy
directions: Mix soup and milk together.
Warm in oven while you brown the minute steaks.
Add minute steaks to gravy and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey-whole wheat bread
directions: Mix whole wheat flour, honey, shortening, salt and yeast in a 4-quart bowl; add warm water.
Beat on low speed, scraping bowl frequently, 1 minute.
Stir in enough all-purpose flour, 1 cup at a time, to make dough easy enough to handle.

title: baked macaroni casserole
directions: Brown pork sausage by itself.
Saute ground meat, onion and garlic.
Add the pork
sausage and the tomato paste.
Cook for a few minutes, then add
tomato sauce.
Fill each can with water and add along with
salt, pepper, sugar and basil.
Cook for 1 hour. Cook macaroni
in boiling, salted water al dente. Drain.
Layer macaroni, sauce
and
cheese
in
baking
dish. Sprinkle cheese on each layer.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Break 1 loaf into pieces in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together the margarine, brown sugar, pudding, milk, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour this mixture over the bread in pan.
Break the other loaf into pieces; put on top.
Cover; let rise for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cup and can dinner
directions: Combine first nine ingredients with 1/2 of the bread crumbs in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend in flour.
Divide dough in half.
Half of the dough may be left in the refrigerator until ready to use.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add eggs and lemon juice and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set; top with sour cream. Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with pie filling and refrigerate.

title: tomato soup
directions: Simmer for 1 hour
the
first 5 ingredients and strain. To juice, add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bring to a boil; cold pack 20 minutes.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: chicken and lima bean casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts about 20 minutes.
Cool and dice into bite size pieces.
Add mushroom soup, mayonnaise and partially cooked lima beans.

title: chicken divan
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange broccoli in the pan.
Top with the chicken, cut in bite-size pieces.
Combine the soup and milk.
Mix well and pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Arrange onions on top of the cheese and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: sugar free pancake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry in corn oil in a skillet. Cook until it bubbles. Turn and cook until done on other side.

title: praline sauce
directions: Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, and butter in a medium saucepan, stirring well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, and let cool to lukewarm.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk and pecans. Serve warm over ice cream.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve on lettuce.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Serves 2.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain.
Add to celery, pepper, onion, catsup and puree.
Simmer in slow cooker until soft.
Add the sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic.
Simmer 1 hour more. Serve with buns.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.
Cooking time:
6 to 8 hours.

title: brown rice
directions: Put rice in a 2-quart baking dish. Add other ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: christmas toffee
directions: In large, heavy saucepan or Dutch oven, melt butter and add sugar, water and syrup.

Cook on medium heat, stirring seldom (with a wooden spoon, just to mix now and then) while the mixture bubbles fast, until it's at the golden brown "hard crack" stage (when a small bit dropped into cold water becomes brittle).

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and butter in medium microwavable bowl on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Spread evenly in crust. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until chocolate is firm. Arrange banana slices over chocolate.
Pour milk into a large bowl. Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes. Spoon over bananas in crust.
Spread with Cool Whip. Refrigerate 4 hours.
Preparation time: 20 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Bake four thin layers or bake 2 layers and slice so that you have 4 layers.

title: white bean salad with goat cheese
directions: Cook parsley in 2 cups boiling, salted water for 2 minutes. Drain.
Rinse with cold water and pat dry.
Put in a food processor with 1 cup oil and puree.
Cover and set aside at room temperature for 18 to 24 hours; strain and discard sediment.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Stir together flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Set aside half of crumbs.
Pat remaining crumbs over bottom of 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla, stirring until smooth.
Add rhubarb and cook until mixture becomes thick and clear.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Crumble remaining crumbs over top of sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy no-bake macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Melt on low heat the cheeses and margarine.
Add milk and stir, then add the pasta and reheat.

title: peanut butter marshmallow toast
directions: Toast bread until golden brown.
Cover each piece generously with peanut butter.
Top each piece with 6 marshmallows.
Set oven to broil.
Cook until marshmallows turn golden brown and begin to melt.
This will only take a few seconds if oven is hot.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: cocoa chiffon cake
directions: Set out 10-inch tube pan; measure and pour into large bowl egg whites.
Allow to stand at room temperature about 1 hour.
Set aside egg yolks in small bowl.
Mix cocoa and boiling water and set aside to cool.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add butter and milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and let cool before serving.

title: crab bites
directions: Mix cheese and butter until smooth.
Add seasonings and mayonnaise.
Stir in crab meat.
Spread onto split (unbaked) muffins.
Freeze on baking sheet for 30 minutes.
Cut into 4 wedge shape pieces (each split muffins).
Freeze in a Ziploc bag.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 48 bites.

title: anne marie's tomato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large salad bowl.
Mix well. Garnish with pieces of curly lettuce.
Serve with crusty old fashioned Italian bread.

title: everett and sandra's alpine chili
directions: Brown meat, chorizo, onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce, water and Mexican beer.
Roast, peel and deseed jalapenos.
Add to other ingredients.
Simmer on the stove for at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, add the 3 cans of kidney beans.
This is great on a chilly day!!
Serve with crackers or crusty bread.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and carrots.
In separate bowl mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add flour mixture to other.
Mix until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch (greased) pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: prune sour cream coffee cake
directions: Pour boiling water over prunes; let stand for 15 minutes. Drain; cut into sixths.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Remove 1/4 cup of mixture; toss with prunes.

title: bean dip
directions: Heat beans; spread in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread sour cream over beans.
Add cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Add tomato, onions and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grape juice crush
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add it just before serving.

title: crabmeat au gratin(serves 6)
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine until onion is wilted. Blend flour in well with this mixture.
Pour in the milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, salt, red and black pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Put crabmeat in a bowl suitable for mixing and pour the cooked sauce over the crabmeat. Blend well and then transfer into a lightly greased casserole and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 or 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: microwave cheesy potato boats
directions: Prick potatoes; place on paper towels in microwave oven, leaving 1-inch space between potatoes.
Cook at High for 15 to 18 minutes or until tender, rotating and turning potatoes over three times.
Let stand a few minutes.

title: pasta and beans
directions: Place in a frying pan and brown garlic in oil and cook bacon, then add tomato sauce and 1 can of water.
To this, add basil and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook this sauce down for 30 to 45 minutes on a medium low heat, then add white beans (cannellini). Cook elbow or broken spaghetti (al dente).
Then drain and add to tomato and bean sauce.
Serve immediately!

title: dump cake
directions: Partially drain pineapple and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered cake pan.
Spread cherry pie filling evenly over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut over cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over coconut, making sure cake mix is evenly distributed over entire pan.
Then sprinkle chopped pecans over cake mix.
Cut frozen oleo into thin pats and place completely (in single layer) over the pecans.
Press oleo lightly with palm of hand.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Let cool and serve.
Yummy good!

title: brown bake
directions: Brown ground beef.
In large baking dish, add browned beef, leaving 1 end empty.
In this end, add sliced carrots.
Layer onions on top of beef and carrots.
Cover onions with sliced potato.
Pour beef broth into dish and cover tightly with foil. Bake in slow oven at 250° to 300° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes and drain on paper towels. Place slices on greased pan, sprinkle tops with grated cheese and grated onion and cracker crumbs. Dot with butter. Either bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or broil until lightly brown.

title: "easy" chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of rice. Mix soup and soup mix in water; pour over rice and chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: fruit almond biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees and coat a cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Combine 1 cup sugar, applesauce, oil, eggs, dried fruit, almonds, and both extracts and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in the sugar mixture.
Form dough into 2-14-inch (1.5-inch wide) logs using wet hands.
(Allow room between them to spread during baking.)
Flatten each log to 1-inch thickness and sprinkle with 1 1/2 tsp sugar.
Bake at 350 degrees until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet & cool on a rack for 10 minutes.
Slice diagonally using an electric knife into 1/2-inch slices.
Place the slices on their sides on an ungreased cookie sheet and toast an additional 8-10 minutes, turning the slices over after the first five minutes.

title: carrot and string bean casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onion and cook until tender. Add flour and stir until smooth.
Next, add milk, salt, pepper and cheese.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and pour over slightly beaten eggs.
Arrange vegetables and sauce in alternate layers in greased casserole dish.
Top with soft crumbs mixed with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots in strips in food processor.
Cook in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in frying pan or electric skillet.
Cook until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add carrot strips.
Cook over low heat until carrots are glazed and heated through.
Stir occasionally while heating.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix together
until
creamy Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a	time
beating after each addition.
Add alternately flour and mixture of water, buttermilk and salt.
Blend well. Add lemon flavoring.	Bake
at
325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in greased and
floured 10-inch tube pan.
After 1 hour, keep checking every 5 minutes.

title: open-faced apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add apples, tossing until evenly coated.
Spoon into pastry shell, mounding in center.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until crust begins to brown and apples are tender.
Remove pie from oven and lower temperature to 350°.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover with soup, wine and sour cream that has been heated and blended together.
Add whole mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: creamy apricot salad
directions: On stove, dissolve pineapple and jello.
Add cold water. Cream sugar, cheese and apricots.
Blend into jello.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl or mold and refrigerate.

title: gator taco
directions: In hot skillet, use 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add remaining tablespoon of oil to 2 cups of gator meat; work into meat well before placing in skillet.
When meat has cooked thoroughly, add onion soup mix and cumin; also add taco seasoning.
Cook until flavors have mingled together.
Taste to adjust salt and black pepper.
Use in prepared taco shells with cheese, lettuce, onion, tomatoes or sour cream, salsa, cocktail sauce, etc.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Slice entire rolls in half.
Put spread of margarine and seasonings (mix together and let set in refrigerator until spreading consistency) on both sides of rolls.
Add ham and cheese. Bake, covered, at 350° until cheese melts.

title: puffy corn fritters(lenten special)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Blend milk and egg.
Add gradually to dry ingredients.
Stir in the drained corn and drop from tablespoons into deep hot fat (375°.)
Fry until golden brown 4-8 minutes, depending upon size.
Drain on absorbent paper towels and serve with maple syrup.
Makes 16-18 fritters.

title: mom's pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt, cut in butter and shortening. Combine cold water, egg and vinegar. Add egg mixture to flour mixture. Mix with fork. Divide in half. Form in 2 balls, wrap in plastic, chill for 1 hour. Roll out one ball of dough, place in bottom of 9-inch pie pan. Trim crust to 1/2 inch edge of pan. Crimp edge. Use second dough ball for top of pie.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Place first four ingredients in a Dutch oven; cover vegetables with water and bring to a boil.
Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender; drain.
Add peas and pimentos; set aside.

title: cherry pineapple cake
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, spread the cherry pie filling, pineapple and 1/2 of the coconut. Put dry cake mix on top of this. Sprinkle the other 1/2 of coconut on cake mix.
Pour melted margarine evenly over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Crush vanilla wafers and add to mixture alternately with milk.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 40 minutes at 325°.
Cool in pan.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package.
Add tuna, soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour in 2-quart bowl.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Flatten each slice of bread with palms of hands.
Cream together cream cheese, lemon juice and egg; spread each slice of bread.
Fold corners of bread over. Dip each roll in melted butter and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 425° until golden brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Heat brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt to simmering over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add popped corn and stir until well coated.
Cool slightly.
Dip hands into cold water and shape into 2 inch balls.
Set on waxed paper. Makes 6 2-inch balls.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat for 3 minutes.
Divide into 2 (9 x 4-inch) large loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done. Cool 10 minutes and turn out on racks to cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan or dish at 300° for 1 hour.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Sift dry ingredients together. Mix milk, oil and egg yolks together.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Fold into egg whites.
Cook on hot waffle iron. Makes 12 squares.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add sliced olives, taco seasoning and enough water to simmer for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Line bottom and sides of dish to form a crust.
Fill with hamburger mixture; cover with cheese, then crushed corn chips.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown (approximately 1/2 hour).

title: spicy chicken with rice
directions: Heat salad oil; add chicken and brown well on all sides. Remove from pan.
Add rice, onion and garlic to pan; saute until golden brown.
Measure juice from tomatoes.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Add liquid and tomatoes to pan.
Stir and scrape up brown bits.
Add bouillon cube, salt, pepper and hot flaked pepper and bay leaf.
Stir to dissolve bouillon cube.
Return chicken to pan. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 40 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 2 tablespoons of sugar. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool.
Whip cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar.
Pour over pretzel layer.

title: cookie crunch(very festive)
directions: Combine dates, sugar, butter, egg and salt.
Cook in pan until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Stir to blend. Form into balls and roll into coconut.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: Heat oil at medium high in large skillet.
Add chicken and stir fry until cooked through.
Set chicken aside.	Combine soup, water, vegetables and basil in skillet.
Heat to a boil, stir in pasta. Cook at medium heat 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add chicken; cook at low heat for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Serves four.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pile lightly into a baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1 cup crushed potato chips. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruity snow salad
directions: Soften gelatin in lemon juice.
Dissolve over low heat until clear.
Blend mayonnaise into softened cream cheese.
Add to gelatin mix.
Stir in gelatin with fruit cocktail.
Add sugar gradually to cream.
Fold in fruit mixture.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all together and bake in shell for 25 minutes in slow oven at 325°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: If meat is salty, boil up in water and drain.
Cook the meat, covered with boiling water, for three to five hours, until tender. When meat is about half cooked, add the carrots, cabbage and turnips.
One-half hour before ready, add the onions, parsnips and potatoes.
Serve with meat in the center of platter and each vegetable separately around the platter.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Crust:
Blend together first 4 ingredients at low speed until crumbly.
Press into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Put batter in bottom of pan and put fruit on top.

title: dilly carrots
directions: Melt margarine.
Add vinegar and sugar and mix well.
Add carrots and dill weed.
Simmer for 10 to 12 minutes.
Pour sauce over carrots and let stand overnight.
Heat before serving.

title: pizza bread
directions: Thaw bread dough, let rise.
Roll very thin.
Put 1 layer of pepperoni on rolled out dough.
Sprinkle cheese on top of pepperoni.
Roll up tightly, tuck in sides.
Make slashes on top of dough to allow steam to escape.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Slice and serve warm.

title: paul's cobbler
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Pour into greased loaf pan or casserole.
Pour in 1 1/2 to 2 cups canned and drained fruit over batter.
Tart Mn. plums or apples with lemon juice added are good. Pour over fruit 1 cup of the fruit juice.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.
Serve as is or with cream (not whipped cream).

title: baked chicken that makes its own gravy
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Arrange chicken in single layer with skin side down in melted butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake until brown, 15 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 325°.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine evaporated milk, soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms to chicken and pour soup mixture over chicken and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover pan with foil and bake 20 minutes longer.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Cream all ingredients together well and pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: world class chili
directions: Cook on low heat and simmer for 2 hours.
May half the recipe for smaller groups or family.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole.
In separate bowl, mix rest of ingredients except for fruit.
Pour batter into melted butter without stirring.
Place fruit into mixture gently, without stirring.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in saucepan; add butter and milk, bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and chill.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift a few teaspoons of flour over nuts and raisins.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add the applesauce which has been heated.
Sift flour with soda and spices.
Stir in butter mixture. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Will make 3 layers or 1 sheet cake.
Bake a sheet cake for around one hour. Grease pans well.
Bake layers at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: easy chicken and fruit
directions: With meat mallet or similar flattening utensil, pound chicken to 1/2 inch thickness.
Sprinkle garlic salt and nutmeg over chicken.
In frypan place margarine and melt over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook, turning about 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove chicken; set aside.
Drain off excess fat.

title: rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening and enough water for a good dough.
Let rise for 1 hour and punch down.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out and place in buttered pan.
For 1 1/2 hours, bake at 350° until golden brown.
Brush tops with butter.

title: apple chutney
directions: Cook apples, sugar, vinegar, garlic, onion and peppers together until sauce is formed.
Add raisins and spices; simmer 30 minutes.
Let stand overnight. Heat to boiling.
Pour into hot jars and seal at once.

title: funny cake(chocolate)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch pan (round or square).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, margarine and salt.
Bring to boil.
Pour syrup mixture over well beaten eggs.
Let cool; add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; then reduce heat to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick praline bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange graham crackers in a single layer in an ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jellyroll pan.
Heat brown sugar and margarine to boiling in a 2-quart saucepan.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Pour sugar mixture over crackers; spread evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans or almonds.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool slightly.
Yield: 24 bars.

title: ranch dressing cheese ball
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix applesauce, margarine, eggs, vanilla and brown sugar well. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mud slide pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in 9 x 9-inch baking dish, mixing well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese in bowl.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding mixes according to package directions, using 1 cup milk for each.
Layer vanilla and chocolate pudding and remaining whipped topping over cream cheese layer.
This looks pretty in parfait glasses!

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar, sour cream, evaporated milk and Cool Whip together and pour over angel food cake pieces.
Mix strawberries and strawberry glaze together.

title: three cheese chicken
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil; slowly add noodles. Bring to a boil; cook 12 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain and set aside.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in soup, milk, mushrooms and pepper.
Arrange 1/2 of noodles in an ungreased 13 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 soup mixture; top with 1/2 of Ricotta cheese and 1/2 of chicken.
Sprinkle with 1/2 Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with Parmesan and paprika.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: quickie pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato chip-tuna casserole
directions: Crush chips.
Add to soup, milk and tuna mixture.
Add onion rings and peas.
Save a few onion rings to crush and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake uncovered in 3-quart dish 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water and cook together until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Then add peanuts and butter; cook in the syrup until it turns brown.
Add vanilla, remove from heat.
Add the soda; mix well.
Pour into buttered pans, spread thinly.
When cool, break it.

title: mother's apple dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, shortening, salt and milk.
Roll and cut in 4 squares.
Pare and halve apples and add cinnamon.
Fold around apples.
Boil together sugar, water and butter for a couple of minutes.
Pour over apples.
Bake until apples test done. Baste often while baking.

title: poncho's chicken
directions: Boil the chicken with some onions, garlic, salt, oregano (and a little pepper) for seasoning. Remove chicken from broth and shred it. In a large skillet, melt 1/4 pound butter. Add the soy sauce and teriyaki sauce and saut the mushrooms until cooked. Add the chicken (with medium-high heat) until chicken is brown.

title: coquille st. jacques
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper. Melt 4 tablespoons butter in top of a double boiler.

Gradually add flour mixture, blending well. Remove the top of the double boiler from boiling water, and place over direct heat. Gradually add half and half, stirring constantly until mixture reaches boiling point. Return double boiler to boiling water and cook 5 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in large cake pan; add cherries.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk.
Add flour into butter and cherries.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.
Can use another fruit (blackberries, peaches etc.).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a shallow, greased baking dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for a bridal shower or any ladies' luncheon.

title: fireside potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, parsley and pimento.
Add seasoning. Brown in hot oil until golden brown and crisp.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: special steak
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Pour mixture over steak in shallow dish.
Cover; refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight to marinate.
Remove steaks and reserve marinade.
In large skillet, brown steak in 1 tablespoon oleo. Add marinade, plus 1/2 cup water.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.

title: roast tenderloin of beef
directions: Request a butcher to provide you with a peeled and roast-ready tenderloin of beef, silverskin removed.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef, chopping finely.
Drain.
Place all other ingredients into food processor or blender.
Blend until onion is not noticeable (kids don't see it).
Pour mixture over ground beef; stir.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on buns.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli into bite-size flowerets.
Chop red onion and set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to make the dressing.
Stir in the broccoli, red onion, golden raisins, bacon bits and peanuts.

title: peanutty-chocolatey popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in large bowl.
Cover popcorn with margarine and toss.
Sprinkle with pudding mix and toss until covered.
Add nuts and candy.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *You may substitute with other favorite fruits, i.e., kiwi, etc.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put fruits in a bowl and add dry lemon pudding.
Coconut and nuts may be added, if desired.
Chill.
Serves 8 or more.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to
375°.	Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
(The
sour
cream	mixes
better,	if
you microwave it to get
it a little warm.) Bake, uncovered for 40 to 45 minutes.
It will
seem a little runny in the middle but it sets up once it's
out of the oven.
You can bake it longer if you'd rather not have it runny.

title: cherry-o cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
When soft, whip until fluffy.
Gradually add Eagle Brand milk.
When well blended, add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust; chill 2 hours before spreading cherry pie filling on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, water, eggs and pumpkin; add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Oil and flour 1-pound coffee cans or coconut cans.
Pour mixture into cans, filling about 1/2 full. Bake at 350°, about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together the pudding, milk and ice cream until the ice cream is melted.
Pour into a cooled graham cracker crust pie shell.
Put Cool Whip over the top of the mixture, spreading with a spoon.
Put chocolate shavings on top of all.
Shavings are made from the candy bar, using a potato peeler.
Cool 10 hours or long enough to let it get very cold.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix well.
Pour in a Pam sprayed 11 x 9-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: barbecue bread
directions: Combine butter or margarine with garlic mix.
Spread on 16 slices of bread.
Wrap in heavy foil and heat for 10 minutes.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Slice onion and artichoke hearts.
After rice is cooked, while still warm, add artichoke hearts, mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Mix well.
Add marinade from artichokes.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate.

title: the cheezy recipe
directions: Combine cream cheese, vanilla and egg (using egg yolk only). Spread 1 package crescent rolls over bottom and halfway up side of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cheese mixture over crust.
Take second package of crescent rolls and roll out on wax paper to size of pan; put on top of cheese mixture and pinch edges.
Beat egg white until foamy; brush on top of crescent rolls.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coffee pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, oil and water.
Add eggs one at a time and beat 8 minutes on high speed.
Add flavoring.
Swirl the last three ingredients through cake before baking.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then remove and glaze.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Finely chop nuts.
Mix with flour. Beat butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl until pale and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour until just blended.
Roll into balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 45 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Place on wire rack to cool completely.
Roll in powdered sugar again.

title: dallas dip
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Then mix together last 3 ingredients and toss with first mixture.
Refrigerate in covered container until ready to serve.
Flavors blend very well if prepared a day or two ahead.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sprouts a la brigoule
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts; arrange in greased casserole; add vegetables and chestnuts to bouillon and cook 10 minutes; add butter, season to taste and add lemon.
Pour vegetable mixture over sprouts and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes. Approximate yield:
6 portions.

title: anything goes cake(allergy free  of milk and egg)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs with mixer and add to dry ingredients.
Mix with wooden spoon while adding fruits and nuts and extract.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 85 minutes.

title: mexicali eggplant
directions: Microwave ground beef at Full power until beef loses pink color (5 to 15 minutes); drain and set aside.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Mix well and spread on cooked pie shell.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: sauce for 5 chickens
directions: Heat over slow heat until well blended.
Do not boil.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Can also add 1 cup tomatoes, 2 hard-cooked eggs and sunflower seeds.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Parboil ribs slightly, then drain off all water and braise in oven for about 1 hour, having added salt and pepper.
Do not add water to roaster pan.
When about half done, brown sliced onion and add to ribs.
Stir ribs now and then to brown evenly.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix well with fork.
Stir in 1 beaten egg into flour.
As soon as the dough becomes difficult to stir with fork, work with your fingers until smooth and is medium stiff dough.
Add flour as needed.
Knead dough a few minutes on floured surface.
Divide dough into 4 or 5 parts.
Roll thin and cut 1 1/2 to 2 inches wide.
Then cut the strips the other way to make about a 1 1/2 to 2-inch square.
Drop into boiling broth and cook 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine sugar and milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Then cook without stirring until a small amount of syrup forms a soft ball in cold water (232°).
Add butter and remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm (110°); beat until thick and creamy and right consistency to spread.
If desired, place over hot water to keep soft while spreading.
Makes enough frosting to cover tops and sides of 2 (9-inch) cakes or top and sides of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake or about 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Butter 8 x 8-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 broccoli, margarine, crushed crackers and 1/2 grated cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Fry bacon and okra in the butter with a little flour until brown.
Reduce heat and add scallions, onions, bell pepper, celery, tomatoes, parsley, gumbo file, sugar, ketchup, salt and pepper and chicken stock.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken, shrimp and crab meat.
Simmer 15 minutes more.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: In mixer, combine cheese and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing well after each.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Reserve 2 cups cheese mixture.
Pour remaining batter into well buttered pie pan or 9-inch square pan.
Add chocolate to reserved cheese mixture.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls into pan; swirl mixtures together with knife.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool, then chill.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles according to their directions and drain. Add warm cream of mushroom soup (strain out chunks of mushrooms).

Add noodles and soup and half of cheese in a 9 x 13 pan along with warm milk. Mix well (if it seems dry, add more milk). Put bread crumbs and the rest of the cheese on top. Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Dab butter on top. Cover with foil for half the time. Cook at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: lemon jello pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat oven to 350°.
Use tube pan (deep pan).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chewy pralines
directions: Combine sugars, Karo and milk in saucepan and boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and almond extract.
Stir until starts to cool and thicken.
Add pecans.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Stir in the crab meat, cheese and green onions.
Pour into the pie shell and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes, or until set.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook the water, sugar, cornstarch and salt until thick and clear.
Stir in strawberry jello.
Cut 1 pint strawberries into a baked pie shell.
Pour cooked mixture over strawberries; chill. Cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: rum cooler
directions: Mix together and freeze for 2 days.
Spoon into glasses.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix brown sugar, chocolate, butter and water. Bring to
a boil and cook 3 minutes. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Add enough powdered sugar to spread.
Add vanilla and nuts. (Nuts are optional.) Spread between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: lo-cal jello salad
directions: Mix jello with pineapple until dissolved.
Add cottage cheese and mandarin oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Use 11 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut on bottom of well-greased pan.
Spread pecans over coconut.

title: "irresistible" chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream together margarine, oil and sugars.
Mix in beaten egg.
Combine flour, cream of tartar and baking soda. Add to egg mixture along with vanilla.
Fold in Rice Krispies cereal, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Roll into ball or drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Press slightly to flatten dough.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust(makes five 9-inch crusts)
directions: In large bowl, mix well with fork, flour, sugar and salt.
Add shortening and mix with fork until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat water, vinegar and egg.
Add to flour mixture and stir until moistened.

title: butter crumb potatoes
directions: Roll whole potato in melted butter, then roll in the remaining ingredients.
Place in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour remaining butter over potatoes (more butter may be melted, if needed).
Cover and bake in hot oven at 400° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are done. Makes 6 servings.

title: steak teriyaki
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Pour over steak.

Pierce surface deeply with fork. Cover and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours. Grill 3 to 4-inches from hot coals, basting frequently, with marinade about 20 minutes (10 minutes each side) or until desired degree of doneness is reached.
Thinly slice steak on the diagonal.
Makes 8 servings, 6 ounces each.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all; mix well.
Allow to set one day to blend before using.
Store in tight covered jar.
Can be frozen in smaller containers.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients in order listed. Pour into pie crust shell.
Bake for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife inserted into center of pie filling comes out clean. Yields 6 to 8 servings. Good with Cool Whip topping.

title: tofu pumpkin pudding
directions: In blender, put tofu, egg whites, cornstarch, molasses and spice.
Blend until smooth.
In bowl, put sugar and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Pour ingredients from blender into bowl.
Mix all together.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Wash berries; drain well.
Place in 9-inch square baking dish. Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt; sprinkle over berries.
Dot with butter.
Roll pastry for two crust pie on floured surface to 9-inch square.
Place one over berries, sealing edges to side of pan.
Cut slits in crust.
Brush crust with milk and sugar.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Bake other crust 8 to 10 minutes.
Prick bottom with fork.
Break into pieces.
Serve with cobbler.
Good with ice cream.

title: refrigerator bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water, then add 3 cups water, 1 tablespoon sugar and salt and let set 1 hour.
After set 1 hour, add lard or oleo, 1 cup sugar, eggs and flour.
Let raise and make in rolls.
Let raise again and bake at 350°.

title: sheepherder potatoes
directions: Fry bacon until not quite crisp.
Add onions and saute until limp.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Center potatoes on tinfoil, placed in large casserole dish.
Pour bacon mixture over potatoes and season with salt and pepper.
Seal foil with small space between potatoes and foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: brownies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and mix.
Add other ingredients slowly, mixing thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate with hot water; set aside.
Combine all other ingredients in large bowl (except nuts and coconut) and beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Blend in white chocolate and beat 1 more minute.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased and paper lined pans.

title: polish pretzels
directions: Cream egg yolks and sugar until blended.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Add salt and baking powder to the flour, then add together.
Work the dough until well blended and if needed, add extra flour.
Roll out dough until very thin, then cut into strips 1 1/4 or 1 1/2 x 3 inches.
Make a slit (small) in center.
Put one edge of the strip through the center slit, making a bow.
Fry in oil (Crisco) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tasty glazed meatballs
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Mix well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook in oil over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Drain on paper towels.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix all fruit together; fold in Cool Whip.

title: orange worms
directions: Wiggle these worms any way you want on your plate!
If you like, give them "eyes" made from licorice bits.
Place apricots in colander and let drain.
Place drained apricots in food processor, cover and whirl until well blended.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Mix gelatins and sugar with boiling water.
Cool.
Fold in fruits and sherry.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: About
1 1/2 hours before serving, preheat oven to 350°. In
a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, milk, margarine, melted unsweetened chocolate, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat at
low speed until ingredients are just mixed.
Increase speed to
medium and beat 4 more minutes.
Batter will have a curdled appearance. Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: hash brown baked potatoes
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix potatoes with sour cream, melted butter, soup, onion and half of cheese.
Pour into pan.
Top with other half of cheese.
Top this with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Very good for parties.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Combine taco sauce and chiles (set aside).
In large frypan cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Add cumin, beans, 1 cup cheese, 1/2 of taco sauce mixture and water.
Pour 2 cups Corn Flakes into lightly greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch (2-quart) glass baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining taco sauce mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cereal.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes, sour cream, chopped green onions and olives.

title: carrot wheat muffins
directions: Measure dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Stir in carrots and orange rind.
In a small bowl, beat egg with milk, molasses and melted butter.
Add to dry ingredients all at once, stirring just to moisten.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: four-bean salad
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in a large bowl; toss gently. Combine next 8 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour marinade over vegetables, tossing gently.
Cover vegetables and chill at least 4 hours.
Serve in a lettuce-lined bowl, if desired.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: decorator's frosting
directions: Mix and beat until fluffy. Spreads easily. Not overly sweet. Use to decorate with pastry tube tips.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles for 8 minutes; drain.
Rinse.
Return to pan and add soups, milk and peas.
Mix well.
Put 1/2 of mixture in loaf pan.
Add cheese.
Top with remaining mixture.
Crush potato chips on top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: red beet chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans. Sift together the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Beat together the sugar, oil and eggs for 2 minutes.
Beat in the beets, melted chocolate and vanilla.
On low speed, gradually stir in the flour mixture.
Spoon into prepared cake pans and bake about 25 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes, then turn out onto cake racks and cool completely.
Spread whipped cream or frosting between layers and all over cake.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Stir together water, oats and oleo.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Then combine all ingredients and stir gently.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in greased and floured oblong pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Season to taste.
Combine soup with meat and
heat thoroughly.
Add Tater Tots, cheese and onions. Bake at 350°
for
to
45 minutes.
Additional cheese and Tater Tots may
be added on top of casserole.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions.
In 2 quart saucepan, heat olive oil.
Cook spinach, onions and garlic clove.
Stir about 5 minutes until tender and clear.
Remove pan from heat and stir in Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt and egg.
Drain lasagne noodles and put in single layer on wax paper to drain and dry.
Evenly spread cheese mixture on lasagne noodles.
Roll up each noodle jelly-roll fashion.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, spoon about 1 cup of tomato sauce.
Arrange rolled noodles seam-side down in sauce.
Top with remaining sauce and sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with loose foil and bake for 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
Be sure the dish is bubbly and the cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and ham quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle ham, broccoli, onion and cheeses into pie crust.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Serve with vegetables.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Combine in food processor or blender.
Excellent over pinto beans.
Refrigerate.

title: prize orange cake
directions: Squeeze orange and add juice to milk.
Put remainder of orange plus the raisins through a food grinder.
Mix other ingredients except egg whites as for a "butter cake".
Add minced fruit and chopped nuts.
Lastly, add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in prepared 9 x 13-inch pans at 350° for 25 minutes or until it passes the toothpick test.

title: walnut delight
directions: Mix oleo, walnuts and flour until crumbly.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Combine 3/4 of Oreo crumbs with the margarine. Press in pan or dish to form crust.
Set aside 1/4 of Oreos.

title: cauliflower pickles
directions: Combine ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil, stirring. Reduce heat, cook 10 minutes, stirring.
Fill hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch space.
Adjust lids.
Process for 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields 4 to 5 pints.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Punch holes in pie crust with a fork.
Bake crust until light brown.
Mix in a bowl water, milk, eggs, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and bake 45 minutes on 375°.
Center will still be shaky.

title: * potato pancakes *
directions: Add dry ingredients to potatoes and mix in eggs well.
Fry in hot grease.
Makes about 10 pancakes.
Good served with creamed corn.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix and cook on high heat the first 4 ingredients until soft ball stage. Take off fire and cool a little.
Beat and add the vanilla, butter, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix well. Pour into greased pan, 12 x 10 x 2-inch. Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into chunks. In a saucepan, saute onion and garlic in butter until soft. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chilies, cumin, sugar, salt, oregano and basil. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove from heat. Dip each tortilla in tomato mixture to soften. Fill each tortilla with chicken and 2 Tablespoons of cheese. Place in a greased 9 X 13 pan. Blend sour cream into remaining tomato sauce mixture and pour over enchiladas. Sprinkle top with remaining cheese. Bake, covered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: down south bars
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex pan (9 x 15-inch) in oven.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour and soda in a medium mixing bowl.
Add pecans and vanilla.
When margarine melts, pour batter over and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
This will rise and fall just about the time it comes out of the oven.
Cool and cut into bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Butter bread and cut into cubes.
Place half in 14-inch baking dish. Combine chicken, vegetables, mayonnaise, boiled eggs and seasonings.
Spread over bread cubes.
Put remaining bread over this mixture.

title: fudge (1)
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler and pour milk in slowly.
Stir until it thickens.
Add broken nut meats.
Pour out on wax paper.
When set, put in icebox and use next day.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook and drain 1 pound sausage.
Mix other ingredients together in a saucepan and melt over low heat.
Add sausage. Serve warm with crackers or chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let stand at room temperature in order to mix together.
Chill well before forming into ball.
Roll in chives or chopped nuts.

title: ice cream cake
directions: In tube or Bundt pan, place half of cake pieces.
Let ice cream get soft.
Spoon half of ice cream over cake.
Pour half of sauce over top.
Add rest of cake and ice cream.
Let ice cream melt into cake (about 1 hour).
Refreeze overnight.
Unmold on serving dish.
Serve remaining sauce over sliced ice cream cake. Delicious!

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° until firm.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg.
Add mashed bananas to mixture.
Add soda and salt to flour; mix well.
Add nuts; mix well.
Pour into loaf pan which has been lightly greased.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix with flour to form a light, coarse meal.
Pat into pie pan and prick with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into thin wedges.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Layer 1:
Mix flour, oleo and pecans together.
Press into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Let cool before adding other layers.

title: easy lemon chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Add soup mix and water.
Bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Cream cheese with sugar; beat in egg and dash of salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Prepare cake according to directions on package.
Fill cupcake papers 2/3 full with cake mix.
Drop one round teaspoonful of cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as directed on package.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together and let set overnight in the refrigerator (if using fresh).
If canning, put in jars and hot water bath to seal.

title: turkey strata
directions: Beat together eggs, milk and French mustard.
Layer in casserole croutons, turkey and grated cheese.
Pour batter over completed layers.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken on bottom of a large baking dish after boiling until tender and chunking into bite size pieces.
Pour Veg-All over chicken.
Mix together the eggs, soups, onion and broth and pour over Veg-All.
Mix mayonnaise, flour and milk and pour over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, 1/2 cup of water, onion and spices in a bowl; mix well.
Shape by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls. Place in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: kansas city barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender. Stir in ketchup and molasses until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring frequently, for 20 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate. Makes 4 cups.

title: cranberry bourbon punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine fruit juices and bourbon.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Just before serving, pour in ginger ale. Make ice ring for punch bowl.
Makes 20 to 25 punch cups.
I always triple recipe for party.
Serve this and always have a happy party.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 45 minutes. Refrigerate any remaining sauce.

title: hot mexican bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Heat in double boiler. Top with crisp bacon, crumbled.
Serve with potato chips.

title: marion hall's biscuit shortcake
directions: Grease 8-inch or 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, except fruit and Cool Whip; pour into tin.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes (don't brown - too done).
Top with strawberries or peaches, sliced and sweetened.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: san antonio beans
directions: Drain all the beans.
Coat a saucepan with spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add green pepper and onion; saute until tender.
Add pinto beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: swiss broccoli soup
directions: Combine ham, onion and broccoli in water and cook until broccoli is tender.
Blend milk and flour together.
Gradually add milk mixture to ham, broccoli mixture, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese and seasonings; cook until cheese begins to melt.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Combine flour, brown
sugar, melted margarine and chopped pecans. Bake in sheet cake pan about 10 minutes at 350°. Stir and keep 1/2 cup of mixture to sprinkle on top of Fluff.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in oatmeal, corn flakes, chips, coconut and nuts.
Drop batter 3 inches apart on ungreased sheet; flatten slightly.
Bake 15 minutes.
Makes thirty 5-inch cookies or 7 dozen smaller ones.
I make half of the recipe which yields 6 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: vermicelli with chunky vegetable sauce(low-fat, lo-cal)
directions: In a large, nonstick skillet, heat the oil over medium heat. Add the broccoli, green peppers and garlic.
Cook the vegetables, stirring frequently until they are crisp-tender (3 to 4 minutes). Stir in stewed tomatoes, artichokes, peppers, sun-dried tomatoes, capers, basil, oregano and red pepper flakes.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Partially cover and simmer until sauce thickens slightly (20 to 25 minutes).
Toss the vegetable sauce with the hot vermicelli and serve.
Serves 6.

title: danish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well; roll in small balls and 1 tablespoon bacon drippings in cooking oil.
While they are browning, make sauce.

title: sloppy joes for a crowd
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix all other ingredients with ground beef.
Place mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook and cool potatoes.
Cut up as for potato salad.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp.
Mix egg, flour, vinegar and milk together after bacon is fried.
Mix all together in pan and cook until it thickens.
Pour over potatoes and onions. Warm to serve.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Saute onion and mushrooms.
Add hamburger and spaghetti and simmer 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: When making a pie, any leftover dough can be rolled out (like pie).
Spread softened butter or oleo on.
Then sprinkle cinnamon and sugar to cover completely.
Roll into a log and cut in about 1-inch length.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 325° until outside is a little hard.
Could take about 40 minutes, depending on which oven rack you cook them on.

title: beef stew
directions: While vegetables are cooking, flour meat and saute until brown.
Add meat to vegetables.
Cook until well done.

title: french toast
directions: Mix eggs, milk, and salt.
Dip day old bread into milk-egg mixture.
Fry in a small amount of butter until golden brown on both sides.
If you prefer, you can place on greased pan and broil 4 to 5 inches from heat until golden brown on each side.
Serve with your favorite syrup, confectioners sugar, or jelly.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain salmon.
Combine with egg, oats, onion, parsley, lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper.
Form into 4 patties.
Pan-fry in small amount of oil until golden brown on both sides.
Spread Gulden's Salmon Burger Sauce on buns.
Place lettuce, tomato and salmon patty on bottom half of each bun.
Top with Salmon Burger Sauce and parsley on the top half of bun.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then remaining ingredients. Refrigerate at least overnight.
Take approximately 1/5 of the dough and roll out on a generously floured surface.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool, then frost.
Easy and very tasty.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine
crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom and 1 inch up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: tomato and eggs
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Drain most of juice off tomatoes.
Add to skillet and if whole, mash slightly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Crumble bacon and add to tomatoes.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into a rather shallow baking dish.
Carefully break the eggs and drop into the tomatoes, one at a time.
With a tablespoon, gently ease (from underneath) down into the tomatoes. Sprinkle each egg with paprika.
Bake in 300° oven until egg yellows are firm.

title: philadelphia stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in margarine; add onion and cook until tender.
Add milk and cream cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper (mushrooms, if desired).
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix eggs, butter and powdered sugar.
Layer 1/2 wafer crumbs in pan.
Add egg, butter, sugar mixture, then unsweetened berries. Then add Cool Whip.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: beef and pepper rice skillet
directions: Brown beef in oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Stir in onions, rice, beef broth, one soup can of water and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and cook over low heat until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Stir in green peppers and pimentos. Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot sweet pickles
directions: Buy sliced hamburger dill pickles.
Do not use crinkled cut pickles.
Drain the juice off one gallon and toss it away and use the juice of the other gallon.
It makes enough for both gallons of pickles.
Drain juice off pickles into a large container.
Add sugar, minced garlic and Tabasco sauce to the juice.
Dissolve in microwave on Low, just to dissolve sugar.
Pour juice back into pickles.
Any juice left over, toss it away.
For seven days turn jar upside down each day and then reverse.

title: cheerios treats
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine in microwave.
Add marshmallows.
