Toss to coat with margarine.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes until smooth when stirred.
Stir in peanut butter. Immediately add cereal.
Mix lightly until well coated.
Press mixture into prepared pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Delicious! Makes about 24.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, oil, pecans and strawberries; mix well.
Make well in center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid mixture, stirring just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Pour into 6 greased and floured 6 x 3 x 2-inch foil pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes for foil pans or 1 hour for larger pans.
Remove from oven and let cool 5 minutes before removing from pans. Finish cooling on racks.

title: darlene's candy
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Spread 1/2 of this in dish and keep the rest warm. Refrigerate dish for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Cut into small pieces.
Heat cream of mushroom soup and water.
Add cheese and let melt.
Pour half cheese sauce and half onions into broccoli and mix.
Top with rest of onions.
Pour remaining sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in covered dish.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cur sauerkraut strips into short pieces.
Stir in sugar and let stand 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.

title: jerry's dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add sauce, water, catsup, salt, pepper and macaroni.
Simmer until macaroni is done.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat 4 minutes with mixer.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cut up marshmallows and place in a buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
Remove from heat and add condensed milk and nuts.
Pour over marshmallows.
Let set several hours or overnight before cutting.

title: baked beans supreme
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until thick.

title: cajun corn meal crusted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, whisk 1/2 of flour with cornmeal, Cajun spice and salt. Put the remaining 1 cup flour, buttermilk and cornmeal mixture in 3 shallow dishes. Season buttermilk with hot sauce. With smooth side of meat pounder, pound each breast to equal thickness. Pat breasts dry and season with salt. Lightly coat each breast in flour. Next dip breast into the buttermilk, then dredge in cornmeal. Heat large frypan over medium heat with 1/2-inch oil. Lay 2 breasts at a time; cook until brown, 3 to 4 minutes. Turn and cook 3 to 4 minutes more; drain on paper towel. Place breast on baking pan. Finish baking another 6 to 8 minutes.

title: eggs lorraine
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Spread butter in pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese on top of butter.
Crack eggs into bottom of pan; break yolks, don't stir.
Add salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Sprinkle sausage over and pour on cream, then sprinkle remainder of cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: healthy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. While noodles are cooking, cook spinach as directed.
Drain well. Combine cottage cheese, egg whites, Parmesan cheese, pepper and parsley flakes in separate bowl.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Place half of cooked noodles in bottom of dish.
Spread half of cottage cheese mixture over noodles; top with half of cooked spinach, followed by half of Mozzarella cheese.
Top this with half of the spaghetti sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix together rice, onion, curry powder, salad oil and vinegar. Chill thoroughly.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Cook tomatoes for about 5 minutes and put other ingredients in. Let boil for about 2 minutes.
Make a thickening of flour and water (2 to 3 tablespoons), boil for 1 minute.
Break piece of bread, add to mixture.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into hot oil and cook until golden brown.

title: cube steak with onion relish
directions: Cut onions into thin wedges.
Saute onions in margarine in large skillet over medium heat until browned, at least 10-15 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar, stir in vinegar, salt and pepper. remove to serving bowl. Wipe skillet with paper towel.
Add oil, over medium heat place cube steaks and cook until done.
Return onion relish on top of steaks and warm up and serve.

title: parmesan yogurt chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray oblong casserole dish with Pam. Place chicken in casserole dish and dribble with lemon juice. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
In small bowl, mix yogurt, mayonnaise, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, thyme and green onions; spread this mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 60 minutes.
Drain off pan juices.
Sprinkle chicken with Parmesan cheese.
Broil until cheese is slightly browned.

title: southern candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Peel, cut lengthwise in half.
Place all ingredients except potatoes in heavy skillet.
Arrange potatoes on top, cut side down.
Cook over very low heat, basting occasionally, about 2 hours until tender and well glazed.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients; add enough water to dip with spoon in hot oil.
Cook until light brown.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add sugar, salt and eggs.
Stir well.
Add cake flour, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In large bowl, blend together cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Gently fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into cooled pie shell and chill.

title: seafood mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 2 teaspoons water.
Mix gelatine and undiluted shrimp soup.
Cook on low heat until not lumpy.
Add cream cheese and cook until smooth.
Remove from stove.
Add remaining ingredients and mold overnight.
Good served on crackers.

title: sugar-free ice milk
directions: Gather, wash and cut up okra into small pieces.
Wash pint or quart jars and fill with cut up okra.
Put seals on jars and pressure cook pints for 25 minutes on 10 pounds pressure and quarts 30 minutes on 10 pounds pressure.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreos in blender and mix with soft margarine. Put into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip. Pour over crumbs.
Beat pudding mix with 3 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese mix.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with Oreo crumbs.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on lightly greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1/2-inch cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan and serve warm as appetizers.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook summer squash (yellow) in salt water until tender. Meanwhile, beat eggs and milk together and break up 2 to 3 plain pieces of bread.
Grate onion and green pepper (or pimento). Shred cheese.
Pour water off squash and add bread, eggs, milk, pepper and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add Accent and 1/4 cup shredded cheese.
Put remaining 1/4 cup on top of souffle. Put in greased baking pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave nachos
directions: Spread nacho chips on paper plate; sprinkle with grated Cheddar and/or Monterey Jack cheese.
Cook in microwave on Medium for 1 to 2 minutes.
(Watch for cheese to melt.)

title: sugared pecans
directions: Roast pecans in shallow pan for about 15 minutes in 350° oven, stirring frequently.
Cook sugar, water, cinnamon and salt to soft ball stage (236°), without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and the nuts.
Stir gently until nuts are well coated and mixture becomes creamy.
Turn out on greased cookie sheet. Separate halves as they cool.

title: scampi
directions: Melt butter in bottom of broiler pan.
Add shrimp, garlic and green onion.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes, turning shrimp often until they are pink and curled.
Remove from broiler.
Mix in parsley and squeeze fresh lemon over all.
Serve with rice.
(If you use one of the boxed rice mixes, the whole shebang only takes about 20 minutes.)
Scallops can also be used instead of, or in addition to, the shrimp.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Blend butter,
Cheez
Whiz, mayonnaise, garlic salt and crab meat.
Spread
on
all
English muffin halves.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Cut
in
quarters.	To serve, run under broiler until hot and
slightly browned.
Serve hot.	May be stored in plastic bags and used as needed.
Makes 48 quarters.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cut together with pastry blender well, except jam.
Press half of crumb mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread jam over crumb layer.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over jam and press down.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix sugars, margarine and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Spread dough into greased 12 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, just until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix together and beat 5 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Put in oven immediately so poppy seed don't fall to bottom of pan.
Frost when cool (optional).

title: nachos
directions: Preheat broiler. Spread beans over chips.
Top with mound of cheese.
Arrange single layer on large baking sheet.
Broil about 4-inches from heat until cheese is melted, about 1 minute. Top each with small dollop of hot salsa and serve at once.

title: brownies for thin people only
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Beat eggs and sugar until thick and light and sugar is dissolved.
Melt butter and chocolate together.
Cool slightly.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Mix in flour. Add chocolate chips.
Spread evenly into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cut while warm into 24 pieces, 340 calories each.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook and debone the chicken.
Season during cooking.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes and heat.
In large casserole dish, layer tortilla chips, chicken, soup mixture, onion and cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: hot papaya sundaes
directions: Cut papayas in half and remove seeds.
In a baking dish, combine butter, lime peel, rum, juice and honey.
Lay papaya halves, cut side down, on top of mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Serve papaya, cut side up, with a scoop of ice cream and top with lime-rum-honey mixture.

title: nutty noodle casserole
directions: Fry together in skillet meat, onions, and mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese, nuts and noodles.
In a large casserole dish put a layer of meat mixture then a layer of thinly sliced cheese, another layer of meat mixture.
Put noodles and nuts on very top.
Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Into a greased casserole dish put a layer of sliced potatoes, a layer of sliced onions and a layer of sliced wieners.
Repeat layer of onion and potatoes.
Pour can of tomatoes on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with margarine.
Bake covered in a slow oven until potatoes and onions are done.

title: chicken-vegetable dish
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Prepare rice according to package directions, except don't use margarine and cook for half the time (do not drain).
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
In nonstick skillet over medium heat, cook chicken strips and onion in margarine. Stir continuously for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the rice and its cooking water.
Add broccoli and garlic.

title: strawberry-rhubarb cake
directions: Blend flour, baking powder, salt, brown sugar and shortening. Add egg and milk.
Press dough on bottom and up sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 6 cups diced rhubarb into cake shell. Sprinkle with dry Jell-O.
Make blended topping of 1/2 cup flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 6 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle over top of rhubarb cake.

title: cranberry freeze
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
Mix together cranberries, sugar, pineapple and walnuts.
Gradually add to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart bowl or lightly greased 6 1/2-cup ring mold.
Freeze until firm.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir oats, brown sugar and baking powder together in bowl.
Add melted butter and egg; mix well. Drop by teaspoon 1-inch apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in deep baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° to 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Add milk, vanilla and shortening; mix until smooth.
Add nutmeats.
Pour into greased 8-inch square cake pan.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on the package.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rhubarb and sugar together; sprinkle over cake mix batter.
Pour whipping cream or half and half over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.
The fruit and custard sink to the bottom during baking and form a nice custard layer.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cover 1 whole chicken with water and cook on stove until chicken falls off the bones.
Remove from pot, skin and bone it. Bring broth to a boil and add the noodles.
Cook noodles until done.
Season to taste.
Add chicken and serve.
Goes good with mashed potatoes and biscuits.
You can also use beef instead of chicken.

title: pork chops au gratin
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Prepare potatoes according to box directions (in 4 to 5-quart casserole dish).
Add pork chops. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until potatoes and chops are tender.

title: mary's cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients well and pour into a greased oblong pan (9 x 13-inch).
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over cake.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top cake with peaches.

title: cheese appetizers
directions: Combine everything together.
Spread on English muffins.
Cut in fourths.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet for 15 minutes.

title: slaw
directions: Mix and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.

title: tex-mex guacamole
directions: Mix avocado and juice in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Lay out beef on waxed paper.
Dice onions and cut bacon in pieces.
Saute onions and bacon.
Place onions and bacon pieces on a paper towel to remove the fat.
Spread thin layer of mustard on beef slices (optional).
Put equal amounts of onions and bacon pieces on each slice of meat.
Roll each slice of meat into a roll and secure with a toothpick.
Brown each piece of meat on all sides.
Pour water over meat and let simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Take meat out of liquid and thicken gravy with flour or cornstarch. Season gravy to taste.

title: christmas fragrance(ambiance)
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a boil.
Turn to simmer and enjoy the fragrance of Christmas!

title: fruit punch
directions: Heat together 3 parts apple juice to 1 part cranberry juice, with a few cinnamon sticks tossed in.
Serve hot.

title: baby plum cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Add oil and the baby food plums to mixture.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg to flour and begin adding the flour mixture to the egg mixture, a small amount at a time.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (check with a toothpick).
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: hot tea
directions: Mix together.
Add 3 to 4 teaspoons to hot cup of water.

title: toasted almond spread *
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Spread mixture into 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake 15 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: poultry and pork marinating sauce
directions: Combine ketchup, oil, soy sauce, red wine vinegar, minced onion, garlic salt and 1 packet or Equal or or Sweet 'N Low in bowl.
Mix well.
Good for pork chops or turkey cube steak. Marinate overnight.
Excellent when grilled.

title: spinach-mushroom pasta
directions: Stack 8 to 10 spinach leaves, roll diagonally and cut in slivers.
Repeat until all are used.
Place in a large bowl.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook 1 whole chicken; take off bones.
Cook corn meal and milk. Add tomatoes, corn and eggs.
Fry onions, garlic and bell peppers in olive oil.
Add chili powder, olives, salt and pepper.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar; add egg yolks, then add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: butter rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix together cake mix, eggs, 1 cup water, oil and 1 teaspoon rum flavoring.
Pour in pan and bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Then mix butter, sugar
and 1/3 cup water in pan and bring to a boil.
Add 1/2 teaspoon rum flavoring.
Take cake out of oven, leave in pan.
Poke holes in cake and pour 2nd mixture over cake.
Leave in pan for 1 hour. Take out of pan.

title: onion pie
directions: Fry onions in margarine until limp, but not brown.
Let cool slightly.
Add flour (just sprinkle over onions).
Add both milks and salt.
Cook until thick.
Beat eggs in a bowl and add to mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Top with another pie shell.
Brush top of crust with milk.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Delicious.
Serve with cabbage or pintos.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onion; drain fat.
Add Spanish rice and stir. Turn heat to simmer and lay cheese slices on top of mixture. Cover and let melt for 15 minutes. Stir and serve with hot bread.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add water, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Make out in rolls the size of pecans.
Place on baking pan sprayed lightly with Pam and bake 45 minutes at 275°.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine pudding mix and 3 cups milk; mix well. Fold in whipped topping and beat with mixer for 2 minutes. In a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread a layer of graham crackers on the bottom of the dish. Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture over crackers, then top with graham crackers.
Spread remaining pudding over crackers; top second pudding layer with another layer of crackers.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fill a cookie press.
Use different flavorings and food colors for different shapes, mint and green for the Christmas tree, almond and red for the heart shape and banana and yellow for the flower or wreath shape.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Put stew beef into a large pot.
Add 2 quarts of water and cook meat for about 30 minutes, then add carrots, onion, potatoes, green beans, corn, peas, beans, tomatoes, tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Cook for another 30 to 40 minutes, then add macaroni. Cook until macaroni is done, then serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook for 1 hour.
Fill jars.
Leave 1/2 inch from top.
Heat 10 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar, then add eggs and blend well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and milk alternately.
Add vanilla. Bake 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan at 350°.
May be baked in 2 loaf pans for approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: delicious dessert
directions: First Layer:
Combine flour, margarine and chopped pecans. Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: dessert cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients. Roll into a ball and chill overnight. Serve with cinnamon graham crackers. Serves 18 to 20.

title: cottage cheese and fruit or vegetable plate(for calorie minded eaters)
directions: Place
lettuce
on dinner plate.
Put cottage cheese on lettuce.
Place
selected
fruit
around
cottage
cheese in a decorative fashion.
Top cheese with French or Thousand Island dressing.
Two ripe tomatoes may be substituted for the fruit. Slice
the
tomatoes and place around the cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: moms french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Store in refrigerator.

title: sesame gingered beef
directions: Toss meat in flour and shake off excess.
Brown beef on all sides in oil, 3 to 4 minutes; drain oil.
Lower heat; add butter, garlic, shallots and ginger.
Stir 1 minute.
Add sherry, soy sauce, brown sugar and beef broth.
Bring to a boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add scallions and sesame seed.
Serve over rice or fettucini noodles.

title: super seafood spread
directions: Place seafood in mixing bowl and break up finely with a fork. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers, chips or raw vegetables.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups of dip.

title: sweet cherrity pie
directions: For Crust:
Mix; put in cake pan and toast in oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until nice and brown.
Stir every once in awhile. Save some for topping on pie.
Press rest into 3 pie pans.

title: deluxe bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Rinse beans with small amount of running cold water to separate and remove ice crystals; drain.
Mix all ingredients except onions in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered 25 minutes.
Top with onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare yellow rice as directions say on package.
Add Mexicorn, margarine and soup in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Cook lima beans and corn as package labels direct. Drain and let cool.
In a large salad bowl, lightly toss with kidney beans, onion and green pepper.
Pour dressing over the beans.
Mix to coat well. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serve on salad greens or alone.
This recipe is very good on picnics.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in an 8 x 10-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° until brown and edges are bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: hot roast beef sandwiches for a crowd
directions: Put meat, vegetables and tomatoes in roaster.
Cook until meat is well done and can be shredded with a fork.
Mash vegetables. Add ketchup.
Cook 3 to 4 hours in 300° roaster or bake in oven. Serves 30 to 40 people.

title: brioche cheddar rolls
directions: Place yeast in bottom of mixing bowl.
Add water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add flour, salt and sugar.
With dough hook fitted in electric mixer, begin mixing.
Add 4 eggs and soft butter.
Mix about 6 minutes or until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Add cheese.
Mix for 1 minute.
Cover with towel and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Punch dough down, if needed.
Roll into size rolls you like. Place on a greased pan.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: orange-buttermilk salad
directions: Heat Jell-O in pineapple with juice until Jell-O is melted. Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill. Serves 8 to 10.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease round pan well. Coat lightly with corn syrup. Cover with brown sugar. Cut each biscuit into 3 pieces. Arrange in pan with the brown sugar. Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over dough. Pour melted butter over dough.
Bake until golden brown. Invert pan over platter or plate while hot. Let set a couple of minutes and remove pan. This allows the caramel to set up. Serve while hot.

title: pumpkin chip muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, pumpkin, oil and applesauce until smooth.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 16 to 20 minutes or until muffins test done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.

title: mary ann's cookies
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together, then stir into first mixture.
Add Rice Krispies and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: molasses pie
directions: Bring molasses and oleo to a boil; beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix flour and sugar with eggs and add to molasses mixture. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° until pie is firm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas and set aside.
Cream the remaining mixture and add bananas.
Cream with the dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in casserole.
Mix together soup, cheese, sour cream, onion and 1/2 butter.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with corn flakes and drizzle butter over the top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken with mushroom soup

title: veal marsala
directions: Cut veal cutlets into bite size pieces.
Coat pieces with Parmesan cheese.
Heat butter until melted.
Brown each piece of veal on both sides and remove from pan to a serving dish.
Melt bouillon cube in 3/4 cup water, add to pan drippings.
Stir to make gravy.
Add 1/4 cup Marsala wine.
Return cooked veal to the pan and cover.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook approximately 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve with linguini and marinara sauce.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.

Place apple slices in pan. Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown. Serve warm and if desired with light cream or ice cream.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine in skillet on medium heat.
Add flour; stir in milk.
When mixture bubbles, then set off eye.
Add salt.
Stir in cheese.
Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Stir sauce in macaroni.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly, approximately 10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix in large bowl and marinate with a large bottle of Zesty Italian dressing.
Let set at least overnight.
Stir occasionally and refrigerate.

title: old fashioned chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in large kettle with water to cover.
Boil, skim off foam.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth and let cool.
Add onions and carrots to broth. Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add peas; drain vegetables and reserve stock.
Measure out 1 cup (save remainder for soups).
Skin and bone chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Combine with vegetables in large bowl.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Stir in 1 cup stock and milk.
Cook until bubbly.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Stir to coat.
Spoon into 10-inch deep pie plate. Cover with rolled out pie crust with several vents cut in it for steam to escape.
Beat egg yolk with water and brush over top. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Pat in baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Cut butter into dry ingredients.
Spread the crumb mixture over the apples.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Take sauce, jelly, vinegar and mustard.
Mix over medium heat and bring to boil.
Add franks, sliced on diagonal, and heat thoroughly.

title: quick and easy bean dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and sprinkle onion on top.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruits together, then sprinkle with pudding.
It makes its own sauce.

title: chess pie
directions: Blend ingredients together but do not over beat.
Turn into unbaked pie shell and bake 35 to 45 minutes in a 325 oven until lightly brown and set.

title: quick grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water and salt to boil.
Slowly stir in grits.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir a small amount of grits mixture into eggs. Return to saucepan.
Add 1 cup cheese, milk and oleo.
Blend well. Pour into greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour.

title: home made bread
directions: Put flour in bottom of dish pan to cover.
Put water, yeast mixture, lard (substitute crisco), and sugar.
Add flour one cup at a time to make dough soft.
let rise.
Place in loaf pans and bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.
Makes six loaves.

title: jenny's walnut candy
directions: Combine sugars, milk and syrup. Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Cool to lukewarm and add salt and butter. Beat until it thickens. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion, salt and pepper in water until tender. Drain.
In bowl combine soup, sour cream and pimientos or carrots. Fold in squash mixture.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle half of mixture into baking dish.
Spoon squash mixture atop.
Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: aunt minnie's tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and egg.
Add syrup and buttermilk; mix well.
Combine spices, soda, baking powder and flour.
Sift into first mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: carrot salad
directions: Slice carrots and cook until barely done.
Slice onion thin and dice pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over carrots.
Better if made night before to marinate.

title: watermelon sherbet
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Cover and chill 30 minutes. Place watermelon mixture in container of an electric blender or food processor.
Top with cover and process until smooth.
Set aside.

title: mcdonald's big mac sauce
directions: Mix together and serve with hamburgers.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers and 1 stick oleo.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix eggs, powdered sugar and 2 sticks oleo. Beat 15 minutes at high speed.
Spread on top of crumbs.
Slice bananas on top of mixture.
Cover with can of crushed pineapple. Cover with large container of Cool Whip.
Add cherries and nuts on top of Cool Whip.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
(Will keep for 6 weeks.)
When baking muffins, line microwave pan with cupcake liners, fill 1/2 full (2 tablespoons each).
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from pan and place muffins on cooling rack.

title: taco salad (chopped)
directions: Put in a bowl, add all ingredients (but Fritos).
Toss.
Just before serving, add Fritos and dressing.
Toss.

title: sausage soup
directions: Cook sausage until brown and drain.
Add garlic, onion, broth, wine, basil and tomatoes to sausage; simmer 30 minutes.
Add parsley, noodles and zucchini to soup.
Continue to simmer 25 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with fresh Parmesan cheese.

title: chief's breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage. Saut finely chopped onion and pepper in sausage, then drain and set aside.

Mix hash browns, 2 cups of mild Cheddar cheese and 1 cup of sharp Cheddar cheese. Mix in sausage and eggs. Add black pepper to taste; no salt needed. Spoon and pack into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; spread remaining sharp Cheddar cheese over the top and bake for 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: big al's dream
directions: Blend with ice; strain.
Pour in sour glass.
Garnish with banana slices and sprinkle of nutmeg.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain well and combine with rest of ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with cheese cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Mix in blender until creamy and smooth.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together, put in casserole dish and cover with Ritz crackers.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, peppers, onion and pimientos.
Add salt.
Stir well.
Cover and let set 3 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix instant pudding and cold milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch or two 8-inch pans with whole graham crackers (not crumbs).
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers. Add another layer of crackers and then the rest of the pudding mix.
Top with a third layer of crackers.

title: triple good bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. In medium saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Beat margarine, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; blend until evenly mixed and crumbly; reserve 2 cups.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of pan.
Spread raisin mixture to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture; pat lightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: fajitas
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and marinate meat 6 to 8 hours. Heat oil over high heat.
Saute half the meat until it loses its pink color, then add half the bell pepper and onion.
Cook until done.
Place in another hot container; turn down heat to simmer. Add tomato wedges and salsa.
Repeat with remainder of meat, onion and pepper.
Serve immediately on flour tortillas.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Add 1 cup corn flakes and stir; layer cabbage, then cheese, combine 1/2 stick butter, mayonnaise, soup and milk.
Pour over cheese, top with remaining cup of flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange bread
directions: *You can use 6 or 8 ounces candied orange peel and 1/2 cup marmalade instead of candying your own.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt to boil in microwave. Boil for 45 seconds.
Add baking soda and stir.
Pour over popcorn in a paper bag.
Stir, then cook for 1 minute on High. Stir again and spread to cool.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cook milk and cornstarch over moderate heat until thick; cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with mixer at low speed for 5 to 10 minutes, until smooth.
Frosts one cake.

title: crab soup
directions: Cover crabmeat with water.
Combine mustard, salt and seasoning.	Add to crabmeat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add additional old bay seasoning if desired.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables, celery and onion.
Drain.
Add cheese and mayonnaise.
Put mixture in casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt the oleo and drizzle over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond toffee ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, coffee, cocoa, cream, vanilla and almonds.
Blend well.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer; add enough milk to fill freezer.
Freeze according to instructions.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; fry in frying pan.
Pour syrup over pancakes with a dot of butter.
If you do not have syrup you can mix 1 cup sugar and 1/2 stick margarine in saucepan, stirring until mixture becomes syrup.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place into a greased 8 x 8 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
If doubled, separate into 2 pans.
For best results use exact ingredient amounts.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken stew
directions: Bring first 7 ingredients to boil and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours over low heat.
Remove chicken; debone and cut into cubes.
Cook vegetables in broth, adding enough water to make 2 quarts, until tender.
Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup water, adding to broth.
Add chicken and bring to boil while stirring.
Serves 8.

title: grandma's tamale pie
directions: Brown meat in oil with onions.
Add tomatoes and corn.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and corn meal.
Cook for about 10 or 15 minutes.
Pour into square or oblong pan and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes until corn meal is done.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Mix soups and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing, onion, salt, pepper, parsley and celery seed.
Add melted butter and broth; mix well.
Spread over chicken and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato soup(for 4)
directions: Combine the ingredients you choose and let simmer a few minutes.
Serve with the crackers of your choice.

title: orange carrot cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add spices and orange rind.
Beat in eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add orange juice, turn into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then turn out of pan and cool on cake rack.
Cover with orange glaze.

title: crunchies
directions: Melt chips and add peanut butter.
Stir in cornflakes.
Mix well.
Drop from large spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Put roasts, water and onion in crock-pot.
Cook overnight. Drain and chop, then add Kraft barbecue sauce and Tabasco sauce.

title: baked chicken in gravy
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Pour melted butter into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken in pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and continue baking until brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 325°.
Pour off excess fat.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook hamburger meat, onion and taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
Mix 1/3 cup of taco sauce with the refried beans.
Spread half of the refried bean mixture in the pie shell, then spread half of the hamburger mixture and top with 4 ounces grated cheese.
Crumble 12 chips on top of cheese and repeat layers of refried beans, hamburger and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with taco sauce, sour cream, tomatoes, etc.

title: grams
directions: Separate crackers in half and place on large cookie sheet.
Put margarine, sugar and nuts in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 3 minutes, stirring often.
Take off heat.
Spread mixture over crackers.
Bake at 300° for about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan onto wax paper to cool.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Pat into a firm crust in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Zest the lemon, 1/2 teaspoon then juice the lemon to measure 2 tablespoons of juice.
Combine zest, juice, vinegar, sugar, oil and poppy seeds in small bowl.
Whisk until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: angel biscuits #1
directions: Blend yeast and water (set aside).
Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add dissolved yeast and buttermilk and blend thoroughly with fork.
Place dough on well-floured board and knead several minutes.
Roll out desired amount of dough and cut out biscuits.
Place remainder of dough in plastic bag and refrigerate until needed.
Cook at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown. Dough will keep for 10 days in refrigerator.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: In a small bowl, stir together mayo, sour cream, garlic, basil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Blend in 1 to 2 tablespoons milk as necessary to reach desired smooth consistency.

title: fudge
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in the microwave until cheese and oleo are melted.
After ingredients are melted, beat with mixer until completely blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: marbled pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 egg in small bowl; set aside.
Mix flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Add pumpkin, margarine, 1 egg and water; mix just until moistened. Reserve 2 cups of pumpkin batter.
Pour remaining pumpkin batter into a greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Add cream cheese mixture and reserved pumpkin batter.
Cut through with knife to marbleize.
Bake until loaf tests done, approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Put all ingredients into mixing bowl.
Mix with spoon until blended (do not use mixer).

Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread batter and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done. (I grease pan well and put granulated sugar in bottom, making sure to cover and shake excess loose, this is used in place of flour.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.

title: sweet and sour cabbage(low-fat)
directions: Slice onion.
Shed the cabbage.
Heat oil in large frying pan over medium heat.
Cook the onion, stirring occasionally, until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add the cabbage, 1/2 cup water, vinegar, sugar, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook the cabbage, covered, stirring occasionally, until soft, about 10 minutes.
Uncover the cabbage.
Raise the heat to high and cook until all the liquid evaporates, about 5 minutes.

title: strawberry cake mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the hot water.
Add the frozen strawberries.
Chill until strawberries stay suspended in Jell-O. Fold 3/4 of the Cool Whip into the Jell-O.
Break angel food cake into small pieces and add to Jell-O mixture until well coated. Spoon into angel food cake pan and chill for several hours. Unmold and frost with remaining Cool Whip.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Heat butter, milk and cocoa.
Remove from heat and add sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well and frost cake.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk to molasses mixture.
Turn into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar. Then add Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into a graham cracker crust. Refrigerate immediately or freeze.
If frozen, let stand until room temperature before serving or until defrosted.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In serving dish, layer the ingredients in order:

title: onion sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°...Mix soup wid buttah 'n spread slices with this...then cut each slice in 5 strips...put on ungreased bakin' sheet...bake 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil well.
Add carrots, pineapple and coconut.
Sift dry ingredients together and add with nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in ungreased rectangular pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Turn oven off, but do not remove cake for 10 minutes. Good frosted or un-!

title: light pasta e fagiole
directions: In a large
saucepan
with
cover, saute garlic, onion, celery and carrot	in
olive
oil	until
tender.	Add
beans, broth, bay leaves, pepper and oregano. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add
tomatoes
and
basil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add pasta and heat through. Remove bay leaves before serving.
Put in soup
bowls
and
sprinkle with the shredded Parmesan.

title: chuckwagon supper
directions: Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions.
Stir in corn.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into a square casserole dish.
Spoon cornbread mixture evenly over beef mixture.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese; mix thoroughly.
Divide meat mixture into thirds.
Pat 1/3 in bottom of 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; cover with half the cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring to boiling point and let boil until it will become brittle when a little is poured in a cupful of cold water.
Pour the mixture over popped corn that has been slightly salted.
Stir the corn constantly, so the kernels may become well coated.
Shape into ball using as little pressure as possible.
Dip the hands in water before forming each ball.
Keep in cool place as they get soft and tough in warm place.

title: banana filled ribbon loaf
directions: Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and orange rind. Mix until smooth.
Tint yellow with a few drops of food coloring if you wish.
Slice bananas about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange 4 slices on a cracker.
Top with another cracker and continue to alternate banana slices until all have been used, pressing together lightly. Carefully turn lengthwise onto a platter or tray.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Combine with spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles according to direction on package.
Drain.
Lay out noodles on foil to keep them from sticking together.
Grate the Mozzarella and Cheddar.
Mix all cheeses together.

title: red satin punch
directions: Chill fruit juices and 7-Up.
Prepare 7-Up ice cubes by pouring additional 7-Up into two ice cube trays; freeze.
At serving time, combine cranberry juice and apple juice in a punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled 7-Up.
Add 7-Up ice cubes.
Yields 35 servings.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Precook carrots, onion and mushrooms until tender.
Warm soup with frozen chopped broccoli until thawed.
Prepare noodles as label directs; drain.
In bowl, mix Mozzarella, Ricotta and eggs. Preheat oven to 375°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish spread 1 cup of broccoli sauce.
Arrange half of noodles over sauce.
Top with half of cheese mixture, then add all vegetables and sauce.
Top with remaining noodles, cheese mixture, then remaining sauce. Bake lasagna for 1 plus hours or until hot.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 10 servings.

title: herb stuffing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except broth.
Add broth, toss lightly to mix.
Make 8 cups or enough stuffing for 1 (12 pound) turkey.

title: cheese pepper bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add 1 1/3 cups of flour.
Add sugar, salt, soda, sour cream and eggs.
Blend 2 minutes on low speed of mixer.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Stir in rest of flour, cheese and pepper.
Divide dough between 2 greased 1 lb. coffee cans.
Let rise covered in warm place for 50 minutes.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from cans to cool. Can be baked in 1 bread pan.

title: easy family meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Chop onions and mince garlic. Heat oil in a large frying pan.
Add onion and cook until soft, about 15 minutes.
Add garlic and thyme and cook 1 minute.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Add other ingredients. Drop from spoon (bite-size) onto ungreased baking sheet.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Bake at 325° for 18 to 22 minutes.
May freeze.

title: steak and potato supper
directions: Dredge steak in flour; brown on both sides in hot fat. Place meat in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish; pour off excess fat. Scrape up brown drippings left in pan and add to meat. Arrange potatoes with meat; sprinkle onions, parsley, salt, and pepper over all; add tomato sauce. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Rinse and pat dry.
Remove stems, chop and set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble. Drain off drippings.
Add chopped stems, garlic and parsley and saute 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese and mix well.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps and place in baking dish. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Spray two 9-inch round baking pans with nonstick coating and dust lightly with flour.

title: aunt grace's pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan (not a Bundt pan).
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove and punch holes in top of cake with a meat fork.
Pour icing mix over top and return to oven for 8 minutes more.

title: beef roast
directions: You will need a Reynolds oven roasting bag (regular or turkey size).

title: dirt pudding
directions: Put 3/4 cookie crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle margarine.
Mix pudding, milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.
Put rest of crumbs over the top.
Chill.
Can decorate top with gummy worms!

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Simmer together until onion and garlic are tender or may use enchilada sauce of choice (mild) and add the canned tomatoes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly; place in loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon for flavor.
Cover with one 8-ounce can tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen cranberry banana salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice in a medium bowl.
Set pineapple aside.
Add bananas to the juice.

title: japanese stir-fry
directions: Heat a little oil in wok, then add about 1 tablespoon pickled ginger.
Stir quickly over medium-high heat, then add cooked meat. Add tonkatsu sauce to taste.
Add vegetables, a little more sauce, cooled noodles, bean sprouts and salt and pepper to taste. This is a meal in itself.
It makes a lot and it's also good the next day reheated for lunch!!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, buttermilk last.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed shells florentine(great to make ahead and just heat before company arrives!)
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Combine in a bowl, drained spinach, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, eggs and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Fill shells with cheese mixture.

title: palm beach potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes (with skin on) until you can put a fork in them easily.
(Keep checking.)
Set them aside to cool.
Peel and mash the eggs.
Cut up the celery and onion into small pieces.
Cut the potatoes into bite-sized chunks.
Put into a large bowl; add ingredients and toss with hands.
Chill and enjoy!

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick margarine. Cream 1 stick margarine with sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add flour, buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Fold in candy and pecans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in well-greased tube pan.

title: p-nut butter pie(10-inch cream)
directions: Heat sugar, salt and milk to just under boiling point (just warm).
While heating milk, mix egg yolks, cornstarch and enough water to make a very thin paste.
Add to heated milk.
Let cook until thickened, about 1 minute.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour into precooked shell and refrigerate.
Can also be used as a pudding without pie shell.
If using a shell, graham cracker is great.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, sift together sugar, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice and flour. In another bowl, mix eggs, oil, pumpkin and milk. Add wet mixture to dry and mix gently to blend. Fill muffin tins halfway and bake 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 18 muffins.

title: butterhorns
directions: Mix together dry yeast, sugar and warm water.
Let set while mixing.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt chocolate and paraffin in the top of a double boiler. Pierce peanut butter balls with a toothpick and dip into chocolate, leaving a small area on top of ball not covered with chocolate.
Place coated balls on wax paper until set.

title: aloha loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in bananas.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Fold in undrained pineapple and coconut.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to cool.
Let set before slicing.

title: chicken cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Mix flour and milk to a thick paste.
Pour into buttered dish. Do not stir chicken and broth in baking dish. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup of sugar, and 1/4 cup of water in a medium saucepan.
Cook until berries are soft.
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water in mixing bowl, stir well.
Add cornstarch mixture to blueberries.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Set aside to cool.
Combine flour, margarine and pecans in a small mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Press dough evenly into a 13-inch x 9-inch x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup of sugar; beat until smooth.
Fold in cool whip.
Spread evenly over top.
Refrigerate until served.

title: tropical apple slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, pineapple tidbits, apple, celery and almonds together well.
Add mayonnaise.
Toss until all ingredients are well-coated.
Serve chilled.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg in bowl.
Press over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: bonbon cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Cream butter until soft; add egg, then vanilla.
Add sifted flour, mixing well. Let chill and roll in balls.
Press flat with fork dipped in milk.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: jerry's chicken casserole
directions: Line a buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish with bread slices.
Top with chicken.
Saute mushrooms in margarine (butter) 5 minutes. Spoon over chicken.
Add water chestnuts.
Dot with mayonnaise. Top with cheese slices.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Mix undiluted soups and pimento and spoon over casserole. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Remove foil, put crumbs on top and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Mix sugar, flour and pecans.
Mix butter and eggs. Combine. Fill greased and floured muffin pan 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Place in lined cupcake pans and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: blonde brownies
directions: To sifted flour, add baking powder, soda and salt.
Add nuts. Melt butter in saucepan; remove from heat and mix in sugar.
Cool. Stir in egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well. Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cool in pan; cut in bars.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Add flour, baking powder and dash of salt.
Add vanilla flavor and milk.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour.
Add milk, salt and pepper; cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Fold in broccoli, onion and egg yolks.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Pour into 2-qt. souffle dish.
Set in shallow baking pan.
Add hot water to pan to 1/2-inch depth.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cut cookie dough in slices, then quarter those slices.
Put dough in mini muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes. While still hot, put 1 miniature Reese's peanut butter cup on each cookie in mini muffin pan.
Let melt a little and then put in icebox.
Let set.

title: cheese-potato soup
directions: Using large pot, saute onion (chopped) in 1 stick butter.
Add all soups and 1 quart half and half.
Cook on low heat for 2 hours or more.
Everybody loves this soup!

title: fresh apple cake squares
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 11 x 2-inch greased pan.

title: eggnog
directions: Mix pudding, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add milk and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: jam cake
directions: Boil raisins in 1 cup of water until dry. Mix and bake for 2 hours at 250°.

title: simple roast goose
directions: Rub goose inside and out with salt and pepper.
Fill goose with sliced apple.
Truss bird.
Cover breast with bacon slices and cheesecloth soaked in drippings.
Place goose, breast side up, on rack in roasting pan.
Roast at 325° until tender, about 20 to 25 minutes per pound, basting frequently with pan drippings. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mac and cheese
directions: In a 3-quart casserole dish, combine uncooked macaroni, milk, onion and 3/4 of the Velveeta cheese in the dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Remove foil and add remaining cheese. Cook for 15 minutes more.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: she-crab soup
directions: Saute vegetables in mayonnaise until onion is translucent. Add flour to mixture and brown lightly.
Add skim milk and whip to break up lumps of flour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, stirring until to the desired consistency.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, fry 4 strips of bacon until crisp. Discard bacon. Saute onions and shallots in bacon fat until tender, 10 minutes. Add balsamic vinegar, wine and oregano; cook for 30 minutes. Stir frequently until the onions caramelize and are golden brown. Blend in chicken broth. Simmer gently for 1 hour; stir occasionally. Season with salt and pepper. Ladle soup into 4 ovenproof bowls. Float the croutons on top of soup and sprinkle with grated cheese. Broil until cheese melts. Garnish with flat leaf parsley; serve immediately. Yield: 4 servings.

title: russian tea(good on a cold day)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; store in container.
To make a cup of tea, use 2 tablespoons of mix to a cup of boiling water.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white until frothy.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt and add to egg white.
Pour over pecans; stir until coated.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Toast in 250° oven 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Melt chocolate and milk on medium heat.
Separate yellow and white of eggs in two bowls.
Beat yellows of eggs; combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add to yellows of eggs.
Add 1/3 cup of chocolate mixture and milk mixture; beat until mixture is smooth.
Add very slowly, stirring constantly to chocolate and milk mixture. Continue stirring until filling is boiling.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and butter.
Let cook approximately 5 minutes before adding to pie crust.
Beat egg whites, adding 1 teaspoon of sugar until stiff.
Spread on pie filling.
Place in oven at 350° until light brown, approximately 7 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until small amount dropped in cold water forms a ball. Beat egg whites in a large mixing bowl until they won't pour out if bowl is turned upside down. Slowly beat hot syrup into egg whites. Reheat syrup as necessary to keep it bubbling while adding to egg whites.
Beat until it loses it's gloss.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Spread at once in large platter. Cut into squares and let cool.
Makes 2 1/4 pounds of candy.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla, beating well.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Stir in oats and coconut.

title: easy zucchini bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 2-inch) pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: country style steak
directions: In an
open
pressure
cooker,
heat
1/2 cup of oil and quickly brown
dredged
pieces of steak on both sides until all pieces
are browned; remove from pan.
Drain remaining oil from pan and replace pieces of steak.
Add enough water to cover and 2 bouillon
cubes.
Cover and bring to pressure.
Pressure for 10 to 15
minutes.
Cool
pot
and open.
Place pieces in dish leaving "gravy"
in
the
pot.
Return
pot to heat and thicken gravy with 1/4 to 1/3 cup of cornstarch and water.
Add a small amount of Kitchen Bouquet to make a dark rich gravy.

title: strawberry frozen pie
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and melted margarine and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend together strawberries, lemon juice and sweetened condensed milk with mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Spread over crust.
Freeze.
May garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Mix the cake mixture and butter to form a crumb mixture. Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Pat the remainder in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.

title: no bake chocolate cake roll
directions: In small bowl, combine pudding mix and 2 tablespoons cocoa. Add milk.
Beat on low until thick.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread 1 tablespoon mixture onto each wafer.
On foil stack wafers on edges to form one long roll. Wrap tightly and chill 5 to 8 hours. Sift remaining cocoa over 2 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Blend. Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Unwrap roll.
Place on tray.
Spread topping mixture over entire roll. To serve, cut diagonally in slices. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: robert redford pudding
directions: Mix and spread into oblong dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: fried rice
directions: Cut meat into bite-size pieces and in large pan brown in olive oil.
Add ginger, onion, garlic and chives.
Stir-fry until onions are tender-crisp.
Add mushrooms and soy sauce.
Push to one side of pan and break eggs in empty side, scrambling them.
Add rice and sesame seed and heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: vegetable hamburger stew
directions: Cook ground beef until browned in a large Dutch oven.
Drain off excess drippings.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Toss all together, pour into greased casserole dish (6 1/2 x 10-inch).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: fajitas
directions: Combine chicken, onion, oil, lime juice, peppers, garlic and salsa.
Marinate in refrigerator 2 to 24 hours.
Grill or broil chicken and vegetables 4 to 5-inches from heat for 5 to 8 minutes per side.
Bring marinade to a boil.
Cut into thin strips.
Divide among tortillas; drizzle with marinade and cheese.

title: punch
directions: This makes 3 gallons of punch to be frozen.
When served, it should be diluted with 4 large ginger ales.
It will serve 100 cups.

title: rice and broccoli casseroleeverton, missouri
directions: Fry onions in butter, combine ingredients and put into a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood lasagna rolls
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in nonstick skillet over medium-high heat cook bacon until crisp, drain on paper towels.
Crumble; reserve.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat 13 x 9 inch baking dish with cooking spray. Combine Alfredo sauce with wine; reserve.
In bowl combine ricotta, shrimp, imitation crabmeat, 1 cup mozzarella, Parmesan, peas, parsley, garlic powder and reserved bacon.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce mixture in bottom of pan.
Follow steps, below.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine beans, onion, brown sugar, green pepper, ketchup, mustard and barbecue sauce in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Cut into small pieces.
Mix all, cover and refrigerate.

title: gold cake
directions: Cream together flour and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time. Add sugar and beat.
Add baking powder, salt and extract.
Beat 2 minutes.
Put in well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: In kettle, bring water to a boil. Add broccoli, celery and carrots; boil 2 to 3 minutes. Drain; set vegetables aside. In same skillet, saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour to form a smooth paste. Gradually add the broth and milk, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil. Boil and stir for 1 minute. Add vegetables and remaining ingredients. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine rice and Italian dressing.
Cover and chill overnight. Add mayonnaise to mixture and stir.
Fold in vegetables.

title: pickled dilly beans
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, water, syrup, salt and turmeric. Bring to boil.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Cook beans about 10 minutes; drain.
Pour hot syrup over beans.
Put red pepper, 2 cloves garlic and dill in pint jars.
Add beans and syrup.
Seal. Process 10 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes 4 pints.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Mix in cream of mushroom soup and pour into casserole dish.
Cover mixture with Tater Tots, topped with grated cheese.
Bake until Tater Tots are done, using baking directions on package.

title: hamburger chowder
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onion, carrots, celery and green pepper.
Cook until tender, but not too brown.
Add beef; cook until crumbly.
Stir in tomato juice, potatoes and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Combine flour with 1 cup milk.
Beat until free of lumps.
Stir into soup mixture.
Add remaining milk; heat, stirring frequently, but do not boil.
Makes 10 servings.

title: black-eyed peas patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Fry in hot oil.

title: crab on english muffins
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients and spread on muffins.
Freeze until ready to use.
Bake at 500° until hot.

title: holiday jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello according to package directions, using 2 cups boiling water.
Do not add cold water.
Pour into large bowl. Stir in pie filling until dissolved.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Chill until set.
Serve with ham or turkey.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking pan and pour mixture over chicken and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla orange cooler
directions: *Can also use ice milk.

title: frozen salad
directions: Soften cream cheese with 2 tablespoons pineapple juice, 2 tablespoons cherry juice and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise. Cut up pineapple and cherries and add to cheese mixture. Whip the cream; fold into mixture. Freeze until firm. Take out of freezer 15 minutes before serving to soften a bit.

title: beer soup
directions: Put beer and sugar in saucepan; heat.
Put milk and cinnamon in another saucepan; heat, but do not boil.
Put eggs, sour cream and nutmeg in mixing bowl; beat with whisk.
Add hot beer, beating rapidly with whisk.
Remove cinnamon stick; beat in milk.
Pour soup into heavy saucepan; heat thoroughly, stirring constantly. Do not boil; it may curdle.
If soup curdles slightly, strain it. Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix as package directs and bake in 2 round cake pans.
Let cool completely and split layers.

title: hot roast beef sandwiches
directions: Bake together 4 to 5 hours at 200° to 250°.
Shred beef.
If needed, add crushed Town House crackers to meat and juices.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Prepare the macaroni and cheese by package directions and set aside. Brown beef, onion, celery and green pepper; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and corn (including liquid).
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add macaroni and cheese and heat a few minutes to allow flavor to enhance.
This will require a large skillet.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until stiff peak forms.
Mix in a small bowl, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Mix pecans in egg whites, then in sugar.
Spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°. After 15 minutes, stir around.
Let cool, then break.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil broccoli until tender; drain.
Arrange stalks in greased 1 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix well (use juice from Ro-Tel to thin, if needed).

title: quick shake pizza
directions: Spray electric skillet with Pam.
Preheat to 350°.
Mix in 16 ounces quick shake or mix in bowl with fork the milk and eggs.
Add flour, salt, pepper and Italian seasonings.
Shake or mix mixture, then pour in skillet.
Add pizza sauce, pepperoni, cheese or whatever else you like on your pizza.
Put on cover and let cook for 15 minutes without lifting cover.
It's quick and delicious.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda. Combine egg, grated orange peel, orange juice and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes until done.
Remove from pan; cool.
Wrap; store overnight.
(I use mini loaf pans and give as gifts.
Just cook less time.)

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter and add fruit (apples, blackberries or peaches). Combine flour and sugar.
Sprinkle on top of fruit.
Pour milk over mixture and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: beef dinner
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Pour off liquid.
Mix in other ingredients, put in greased baking dish.
Make at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauerkraut
directions: Brown hamburger, green pepper and onions together; drain.
Add brown sugar and tomatoes.
Combine with sauerkraut and cook in a slow cooker or crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and Milnot; bring to a boil.
Let boil for 7 minutes.
Add chocolate chips; beat.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: chocolate pudding pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix dough as directed.
Press into a greased pizza pan or stone.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until set; cool.
In a mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding mix on medium speed for 2 minutes.
In another bowl mix cream cheese until smooth. Spread cream cheese over cookie crust, then spread pudding over cream cheese layer .
Refrigerate for 20 minutes or until set. Spread whipped topping on top of pudding and sprinkle with chocolate chips.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Brown meat, breaking into small pieces.
Add garlic, onion and salt.
Cook five minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 20 minutes, or until thick.
Spoon onto toasted hamburger buns.
Serves 6.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add together and mix well.
Add carrots and pecans. Stir well.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes in 3 layer pans.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Boil meat in water until tender.
Add the remainder of ingredients and simmer for 50 minutes.
Add water if too thick.

title: cabbage beef casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and place in a baking dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice.
Pour over cabbage.
Mix in soup and water. Pour over entire casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Add more water, if needed.

title: chili sauce
directions: Skin and cook tomatoes until soft; drain well in colander. Put green peppers and onions through food chopper.
Add to tomatoes plus salt.
In a cheesecloth, place cinnamon, pickling spices, mustard seed, nutmeg and cloves.
Add to vegetables along with sugar and vinegar.
Cook 30 minutes; remove spice bag and seal in steamed jars.
Makes 5 pints.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Add garlic and salt and cover mixture with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly and let stand 3 hours; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers. Heat to boiling point and seal.
Yields 8 pints.

title: rich vanilla ice cream
directions: Prepare home freezer according to directions.
In saucepan, beat eggs well; add sugar and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, just until mixture reaches boiling point.
Cool, beating occasionally with rotary beater.
When cool, add the cream and vanilla.
Pour into freezer and freeze as directed.

title: peaches on cream cheese cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased 9-inch deep dish or 10-inch pie pan.

title: caramels
directions: In large pot, combine sugar, syrup, salt and 2 cups cream; cook over medium-high heat to 240° on a candy thermometer.
Add 1 cup cream and boil to 240°.
Add last 1 cup cream and boil again until 240°.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans (if desired) and pour into well buttered baking sheet.
Cut into 1-inch squares and wrap individually in plastic wrap. (This is the hard part.)

title: mulled cider(serves 20)
directions: Tie cloves, cinnamon and allspice in cheesecloth bag.
Add sugar, spices and cider.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 15 minutes. Dispose of cheesecloth.
Serve.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk together until thick and smooth; cool. Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled flour and milk mixture and stir until smooth.

title: greek bow tie pasta salad
directions: Cook bow ties in salted water until al dente.
Rinse and leave at room temperature.
Cube raw chicken.
Heat olive oil and cook chicken until just barely done.
Add garlic to the chicken and olive oil mixture after it has been removed from stove as to not burn the garlic.
Allow garlic flavor to permeate chicken for a few moments.
Pour chicken, oil and garlic mixture into pasta. Add all remaining ingredients except Parmesan.
Allow pasta to sit for a few minutes.
The amount of Parmesan added to the pasta depends on how oily the pasta salad is, as the Parmesan is absorbed into the oil.
Too much Parmesan will result in a dry salad.
The salad should be served at room temperature and is best if it is served before it has been refrigerated.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; add enough Hellmann's mayonnaise to stick all together.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in oblong baking dish and cover top with ketchup.
Bake at 400° for approximately 1 hour.
I put foil over the top for the first 1/2 hour, then uncover to let brown.

title: chunky chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender. Let cool. Cut chicken up in bite-size chunks. Add chopped celery and almonds. Cut grapes in half and add to other ingredients. Add Miracle Whip and mayonnaise. Blend all together. Makes approximately 10 sandwiches.

title: english trifle
directions: Split the ladyfingers or sponge cake in two and spread jam on the bottom of a square glass baking dish.
Mix orange juice and sherry flavoring; pour over cake.
Sprinkle with macaroons and cover with Rich Custard.
Allow to set.
Whip cream and confectioners sugar; add vanilla and spread over custard. Decorate with toasted almonds.

title: mom's potato casserole
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed on box.
Soak onion and parsley in water.
Combine potatoes, sour cream, cream cheese, onion, parsley flakes and garlic powder.
Melt butter to put on top. Sprinkle chives and paprika on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: one skillet spaghetti
directions: In a
skillet,	brown
meat
and
onion over high heat; drain. Stir
in tomatoes with liquid and all remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Heat the mixture to boiling, cover and reduce heat.
Simmer, stirring frequently, until spaghetti is tender, about 30 minutes.
If necessary, add additional water during cooking.
Sprinkle	with
cheese,
cover and heat only until the cheese melts, about 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: blueberry muffins(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: stuffed rolls
directions: Mix well and put inside small French rolls.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry glazed pie
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in a saucepan over medium heat and cook constantly 1 minute or until thickened. Stir in strawberry gelatin until dissolved. Remove from heat; chill 2 hours. Arrange strawberries in pie shell and pour gelatin mixture over strawberries. Chill until set. May take about 4 hours. Serve pie with whipped cream.

title: stuffed fish
directions: Saute vegetables in 2 tablespoons butter or oil.
Stir in crumbs and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Place half of the flounder in greased (Pam) 1 1/2 quart (10 x 7-inch) glass pan. Brush with half of the lemon juice. Spoon mixture on top.

Layer rest of fish on top of vegetable mixture. Brush balance of lemon juice on top. Drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted butter (or 2 tablespoons olive oil). Sprinkle paprika on top. Cover with aluminum foil and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until fish flakes when tested. Serve from baking dish.
Delicious and easy!

title: lasagna
directions: Layer 9 x 12-inch pan, starting with sauce, noodles, Ricotta (with egg, salt, pepper and grated cheese added to it). Finish with dry noodles, then sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool for about 15 minutes before cutting.

title: easy to eat peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water
until
it
threads and then add peanuts.
Cook until tan in color; add paraffin and baking soda. Mix and pour quickly on
a buttered cookie sheet.
When cool, break in small pieces.

title: angel salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Add cream cheese into the hot gelatin mixture.
Measure drained juice from pineapple and add water (if necessary) to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add this, the marshmallows and pineapple to the mixture of gelatin and cream cheese.
Let congeal.
Fold whipped topping into the gelatin-fruit mixture. Add nuts.
This recipe makes a large bowl full of delicious salad.

title: pizzowich
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Great on French bread as sandwiches.
Can add more vegetables and use as a topping for your homemade pizza.
In airtight container, Pizzowich keeps for up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: dill dip
directions: Stir all this together.
Serve chilled.
Eat with sliced cauliflower, carrots, broccoli, celery, green peppers or other vegetables, so people will think they're eating healthy.

title: basic cookies
directions: Cream butter well with dark brown sugar.
Add eggs, pancake syrup, and cinnamon.
Stir well.
Add self-rising flour, oatmeal, and raisins.
Stir and drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
(No need to grease the cookie sheet, but a very light spraying of Pam is good.)
Bake at 350° for 7 - 10 minutes (ovens vary).

title: crab dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill and serve with crackers or breadsticks.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Season and cook chicken in water. Have at least 1 1/2 quarts broth/water to cook spaghetti. Drain spaghetti after cooking. (Reserve broth to add to casserole if too dry.) Add chopped Ro-Tel tomatoes. Saute onion and bell pepper in butter and add to spaghetti; mix well. Add mushrooms and Velveeta and cook on stove top in spaghetti until cheese is melted.
