Mix well and add chopped chicken; mix well. Pour into greased 13 x 9 casserole dish. Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes. Freezes well before baking.

title: freezer dumplings
directions: Measure flour in bowl.
Melt margarine and let cool.
Beat egg and milk together.
Add cool margarine to egg and milk.
Add this mixture to flour and mix.
Roll into 3 balls and refrigerate for 10 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Really easy, fast and delicious.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Add ingredients in order listed, mixing well after each addition.
Bake in a lightly greased Bundt pan at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Allow cake to cool in pan for 15 minutes, then turn out onto rack to finish cooling.
May be frozen.
tags: Betty Crocker chocolate fudge cake mix

title: raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease or paper line 12 muffin cups. Combine milk, oil and egg in bowl; stir in cereal.
Combine flour, sugar and baking powder in separate bowl.
Add cereal mixture to flour mixture; stir until moistened.
Drop in muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 12.

title: easy pepper cups
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients except green peppers. Spoon into green pepper halves; chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: *Boil fresh broccoli; defrost frozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with Rice Krispies.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar, lemon rind, orange rind and orange juice in large saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer 4 minutes until cranberry skins pop.
Remove from heat.

title: doily stiffener
directions: Slice 12 lemons into a gallon container; add 2 pound Epsom salts and 1 tablespoon of cream of tartar.
Fill container with lukewarm water; let stand 2 to 3 days.
Drink 2 ounces twice a day.
If it laxatives too much, cut down.
The body will adjust or take once a day or every other day.
It has helped many.

title: lime and honey broiled chicken
directions: Combine lime juice, margarine, honey and garlic powder in a small saucepan.
Heat until margarine is melted.
Stir in wine.

title: hershey syrup brownies
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise and place in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Make pudding and pour over Twinkies.
Slice bananas and strawberries and layer over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: vidalia sweet onion-sausage casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of onions in bottom of 12 x 7-inch glass dish.
Add crushed crackers, then sausage meat.
Add rest of sliced onions. Combine soup and salts and cover other ingredients in casserole. Top with layer of cheese and pimentos.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: merl's strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add boiling water and stir until clear and thick.
Add jello and mix well.
Let cool.
Add strawberries to custard.
Pour into cooked pie shells.
Chill. Top with Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Put in crock-pot with cocktail hot dogs or sliced hot dogs and simmer.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with chicken.
Prepare dressings as directed on boxes.
Use chicken broth instead of water and add butter.
Spread soup over chicken then add dressing for top layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Make 2 layers cake from a cake mix.
Split the layers and put together with filling.
Cover the cake with filling mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: hash brown surprise
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, cheese, soup, onion and margarine in large bowl.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until brown.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks and milk.
Let come to a boil in saucepan.
Pour 1 cup sugar in a skillet and brown.
Pour in the saucepan mixture into the skillet and cool until thick.
Add butter.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell and top with meringue. Brown in a hot oven.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, salt, 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 can of the onion rings.
Add broccoli to the mixture.
Place mixture in baked pie shell.
Cook in microwave oven for 12 minutes on High rotating dish every 4 minutes.
Remove and put remaining cheese and onion rings on top and return tot he microwave on Medium heat until cheese melts.

title: pink party jello salad
directions: Heat liquid and dissolve jello and gelatine.
Add marshmallows and stir over medium heat until melted.
Cool, then add remaining ingredients, folding in Cool Whip last.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: cheese corn muffins
directions: If using corn flakes, crush to yield 1 cup crumbs.
In large bowl, combine crumbs, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and shredded cheese; mix well.
Beat egg with milk and melted oleo. Add all at once to flour mixture and stir only until moistened. Spoon into 9 greased 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Makes 9 muffins.

title: chocolate chestnut cake(serves 20)
directions: Have egg whites at room temperature.
Begin to beat slowly with cream of tartar in a very clean bowl.
When the whites are frothy, gradually add in the sugar.
Beat until the whites are very stiff. Add in vanilla, then quickly fold in chestnut flour by hand by sifting it over the whites and folding with a wire whisk or rubber spatula.
Bake on 2 1/2 sheets (11 x 18-inch) which have been buttered and lined with parchment paper or tinfoil which has been buttered and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour or so until lightly browned and crisp.

When cool enough to handle, carefully turn out of the pan by sliding a metal spatula around the edges of the pan and carefully sliding under the parchment or tinfoil. Carefully peel off the paper and using a serrated knife, cut the meringues into 6 equal pieces, 11 x 6-inch.
If the meringue breaks a little, don't panic.
You can fit the pieces together like a puzzle during assembly of the cake.

title: sausage cheese rolls
directions: Mix cheese and sausage well, then add Bisquick mix, a little at a time.
Mix well.
Make into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, or until brown.

title: english toffee candy
directions: First, spread 1 3/4 cups pecans on waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Cook sugar, butter, vanilla and salt to hard crack stage, 300°, on candy thermometer.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Cream pineapple and cream cheese together.
Add apples, nuts and cherries, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: hot snack food
directions: Cook in slow cooker on low for 2 hours.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Serve hot with toothpicks.

title: pastry or pie crust
directions: Add milk to egg yolks to make 2/3 cup.
Mix all ingredients. Very wet dough.
No.
Fail.
Makes double crust for pie or approximately 4 pastries.

title: quick lunch salad
directions: Blend and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Put nuts and syrup in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Cut biscuits in 4 and put on top.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are light brown. Turn upside down on a cookie sheet.

title: baker's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, sugars, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2-inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: baked squash
directions: Crumble cornbread in a large bowl.
Add drained, boiled squash, 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese and rest of ingredients. (Reserve 1/2 cup cheese for top of casserole during last 10 minutes of baking.)

title: baked apple pancakes
directions: Combine pancake mix, milk, oil and egg. In an 8-inch ovenproof skillet, melt butter. Stir in brown sugar and apple slices. Saute until sugar is dissolved. Pour batter over apple mixture. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until bubbles form on top of pancake.

title: double fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and butter in microwave. Stir in sugar.
Mix in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour. Put in greased pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Add pumpkin; mix well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Beat, alternating each egg.
Fold in chips and grated chocolate bar.
Bake in well-greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: popeye soup
directions: Fry garlic in olive oil; add spinach, stirring to separate and unthaw.
Add onion and green pepper; fry slightly.
Add black-eyed peas (juice too), corn, crushed tomatoes, salt and pepper; cook, stirring often, about 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat Jell-O and pineapple; set aside to cool, then add 2 cups buttermilk.
Mix well.
Let it set well.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour in casserole dish.
Refrigerate.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: hot macaroni salad(good cold too)
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water and salt.
Drain and continue to prepare macaroni and cheese according to package.
Stir in remaining ingredients except onion rings.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with onion rings and bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: tomato jam
directions: Scald, peel and dice 4 cups tomatoes. Put in pot with 2 boxes Sure-Jell. Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Add 7 cups sugar and boil rapidly for 4 or 5 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent floating fruit. Fill hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: sherry's dump it in deer soup
directions: Either bake or pressure cook stew meat until tender.
Brown deer meat in 1/4 cup water.
Be sure to use large kettle.
Add all chopped vegetables.
Open and drain canned vegetables.
Add to soup mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and cover with water. Cook about 5 hours on medium heat.
Stir occasionally.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots and salt and let stand 1 hour.
Drain. Combine remaining ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over vegetables.
Add 1 chopped green pepper, 3 ribs chopped celery and 1 small chopped onion and mix again.
Package and freeze.
To thaw, place in refrigerator overnight.

title: coconut fruit squares
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Combine milk, rind and juice in large bowl.
Fold in 3 1/2 cups Cool Whip and 1 1/2 cups coconut. Spread half the mixture over crumbs.
Arrange a layer of fruit; spread on remaining mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut. Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut into squares.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: lemon spectacular
directions: Mix flour, melted butter and nuts; press in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, then other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop in hot fat.

title: greek feta casserole
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, bring water to boiling; add macaroni. Reduce heat slightly.
Cook in gently boiling water for about 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.

title: southern bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a shallow 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with whipping cream or a lemon sauce.

title: greek lemon chicken
directions: Trim off and discard visible fat from chicken.
Pat chicken dry with paper towels and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a large nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, heat the oil.
Add thighs and cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side, until lightly browned.
Pour artichoke hearts and their marinade over chicken. Lay lemon slices on top.
Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, until chicken is cooked through.

title: brownies
directions: Beat butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour slowly, then vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix well the peanut butter, sugar and egg.
Press into greased 10 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle generously with chocolate chips.
Cover with foil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove foil and spread chocolate over surface.
Cut into bars.

title: butterscotch cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In medium saucepan, combine milk and water; mix well.
Stir in pudding mix. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla, then pudding mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 50 minutes, until golden brown around edge.
Center will be soft.
Chill; garnish with whipped cream.

title: glazed onion rings
directions: Peel onions and cut into even slices.
Heat the butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Add onions and toss for a few minutes until coated with butter.
Do not brown.
Add vinegar, brown sugar and curry powder.
Stir, blending well.
Add parsley. Cook onions for about 5 minutes, covered.
Remove cover.
Cook onions for 2 or 3 more minutes until glazed.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Serve onions hot as a side dish or cool as an appetizer.

title: black bottom cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan or larger rectangular pan.

title: simple blueberry cobbler
directions: Pour pineapple in bottom of 9 x 12 pan. Pour blueberries in pan. Pour dry cake mix on top of blueberries. Sprinkle pecans over cake mix. Place butter pats over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream. Top with Cool Whip (optional).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in saucepan until vegetables are tender (about 10 minutes). Alternate layers of squash and bread crumbs in baking dish, finishing with bread crumbs. Combine soup with 1/4 c. water and pour over bread crumbs. Bake in 350 oven for about 20 to 2 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place breasts
in a brown cooking bag; add lemon juice. Sprinkle garlic
salt over breasts.
Place slices of butter on top.
Close
bag and cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve chicken over
wild	rice.
Pour
some
of garlic butter liquid over chicken and rice.

title: chicken-corn-noodle soup
directions: Cook the chicken until tender.
Bone and chop.
Cool broth and take off fat. You should have about 2 quarts broth.
If you need add bouillon and water to make 2 quarts.
Heat broth and add the carrot, celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Then add the noodles; cook until they are done.
Then add the corn and chicken. Heat to boiling.
This freezes very well.

title: kissing cake
directions: Mix together hot water, dates and baking soda.
Let stand until cool.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Add date mixture. Spoon half batter into a greased angel food pan.
Top with half of the nuts and kisses.
Add the rest of the batter.
Add remaining nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Increase heat to 375° for 15 minutes longer.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Add butter.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
May add paprika or chives. Make ahead recipe.
Very elegant and tasty.
Place in heated oven for 20 minutes when ready to serve dinner.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix with Italian vinegar and oil.

title: orange salad
directions: Stir together milk and Jell-O first.
Stir in remaining ingredients in large bowl, stirring well.
Pour entire mixture into serving bowl.
Garnish with pecans.
Cover and let chill in refrigerator.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Bake in 3 round pans (greased and floured) for 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Duncan Hines Homestyle Dark Chocolate Frosting.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Combine the crabmeat with the mayonnaise, herbs and seasonings.
Spread on rounds of toast and serve immediately. Serves 16.

title: quick chocolate cola cake
directions: Beat cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and oil at low speed until blended.
Gradually add cola to batter, beating at low speed. Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Spread warm Chocolate-Cola Frosting over top of warm cake.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: savory broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water just until tender. Combine eggs, milk, soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Stir in cooked, drained broccoli.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: polenta
directions: Old Method:
Bring water and salt to a boil in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add corn meal slowly and cook slowly, stirring constantly, for about 20 minutes.
Mixture will be thick and smooth.
Turn onto a large platter.
Serve with a meat or tomato sauce.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.
Let cool and pour over first mixture.

title: far east turkey chow mein
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter; stir in curry powder. Saute celery, onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in flour; remove from heat.
Gradually stir in cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cook 2 additional minutes.
Add bean sprouts, turkey, soy sauce and pimento; cook until heated through.
Serve immediately over warmed chow mein noodles.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Whip eggs into cooled margarine.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pie is done when knife comes out clean.

title: holly taters
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potatoes.
Cut potatoes into wedges.
Roll or shake potatoes in mixture.
Place in a baking dish.
Spoon melted margarine over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: coffee punch
directions: Heat water to boil and add coffee and sugar.
Cool and add chocolate syrup, vanilla and milk.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: codfish gumbo
directions: Heat Crisco oil in large saucepan; add okra.
Saute on medium heat for 2 minutes; add onion and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and undrained tomatoes; heat on low for 5 minutes; add corn, black pepper and cayenne.
Lay cod steaks on top of vegetable mixture, spooning mixture over them.
Cook gently 5 to 10 minutes or until the fish is done.
Serve over hot rice.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Wash the cauliflower and break into florets.
Combine cauliflower and next 3 ingredients, tossing gently.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables and toss until well covered.
Chill before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, then move pies to bottom rack of oven and bake 15 more minutes or until firm.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Combine flour and salt, set aside.
Cream butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add molasses; mix until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls; place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Dust or roll warm cookies in powdered sugar.
Yield: about 5 dozen.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Peel off outside leaves of cabbage and onion.
Grate the 2 together and place in a large bowl.
Mix well.
In saucepan, combine vinegar, salt, pepper, oil and sugar.
Bring to a boil and pour boiling hot over the vegetables.
Do not stir.
Allow to sit undisturbed for 1 1/2 hours, then toss and mix.
Store in refrigerator at least 12 hours before serving.

title: vegetable chili
directions: About one hour before serving:
In 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepot, over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook carrots, celery and onion until golden, stirring frequently, about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut potatoes into 3/4-inch chunks.
Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.

title: ellen hayes' cheese dollars
directions: Mix all ingredients together, blending thoroughly, and form a large ball.
Pinch off marble-sized balls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Press out flat with a fork if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: california dip
directions: In small bowl, blend all ingredients.
Chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1/4 c. margarine.
Mix corn flakes with 1/4 c. margarine.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until slightly brown.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Smooth out in the bottom of a baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: bacon-pea salad
directions: Cook bacon until crumbly.
Add with remaining ingredients and chill before serving.

title: drunk dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients, but smokies. Then add smokies. Simmer 1/2 hour on top of stove at medium heat.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add enough buttermilk to make a stiff dough.
Add onions and eggs, mixing thoroughly.
Form into balls and fry in deep fryer or skillet until brown.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini on low heat until clear in color, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sugar, pineapple and lemon juice; cook 10 minutes after it starts to boil.
Add Sure-Jell and cook 1 minute after it comes to a full boil.
Add apricot jello; stir well.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.
Makes a great ice cream topping.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and Velveeta in microwave on Medium-high until all melted.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pat into pan.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, salt and soda.
Stir into cream mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill at least one hour.
Shape dough into balls.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon, mixing well.
Roll each ball in cinnamon mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten cookie slightly.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in remaining 5 ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Great on chicken, ribs and pork.

title: chippy chicken(children's)
directions: Mix potato chip crumbs, garlic salt and pepper in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken parts in melted margarine.
Coat with potato chip mixture and place skin side down in baking dish.
Bake for one hour at 375°.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients, except crumbs or chips.
Alternate with layers of noodles in greased baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs or chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate decadence
directions: Melt
chocolate and butter together.
Mix egg yolks and sugar. Add
coffee
and liqueur to chocolate mixture.
Chill. Beat
egg whites to meringue and fold into mixture.
Put into flat
cake pan
and
bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix the above ingredients and spread in a 13 x 9 inch pan.

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients; set aside. Roll out crescent roll dough, sealing all creases and perforations. Use pizza cutter to slice dough into 24 equal squares. Lightly grease and flour a mini muffin pan; place a square of dough into each muffin cup. Fill each with ham mixture. Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until golden. Makes 2 dozen.

title: camper's hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Mix 3/4 cup hot water to 1/4 cup mix.

title: peach preserves
directions: Combine peaches, lemon juice, butter and 2 cups sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add 2 more cups of sugar and boil for 10 minutes more.
Remove from heat; put into large bowl.
Let stand overnight.
Seal in jars next day.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients in order.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: busy day macaroni
directions: In 2-quart glass casserole, crumble ground beef.
Microwave 5 minutes at 100% power.
Stir twice to break up ground beef; drain fat.
Add sauce, uncooked macaroni and water to casserole. Microwave for 13 minutes, covered at 100% power; stir once. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Let stand, covered for 5 minutes.

title: "richard's" chicken bog-a-lot
directions: Start with 28 cups of water in a large pot (this will result in 26 cups of broth*).
Chop onions and celery and add to water. Add salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and then add raw chicken on bone. Cook until chicken is done.
Remove from heat.

title: mississippi ice cream or cheese grits
directions: Cook
grits
according	to package directions, stirring several times
during
cooking.
Remove
from heat and add all other ingredients,	adding eggs last to prevent lumping.
Stir well to mix.
Add
all
of	the grits and mixture to a greased baking dish and
bake
at 400° for 30 minutes or microwave for approximately
minutes, depending on watts.
Great substitute for potatoes with meal.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Boil
skinned
and
boned chicken.
Cut up and place in baking dish.
Mix chicken soup and broth, heating and stirring until smooth.
Set aside.
Mix margarine, salt, pepper, baking powder, milk
and
flour;
mix well.
Pour broth mixture over chicken, then pour flour mixture over that.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: mexican chicken tortillas
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Dice chicken and set aside.
Mix soups, milk and chili in saucepan and heat.
Tear your tortillas into strips.
In Pyrex dish, layer tortillas, chicken and sauce. Heat in oven at 325° until warm.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Combine cheeses, broccoli, mushrooms and herbs in food processor and chop coarsely.
Add cottage cheese just to blend. Add more seasoning if desired.
Oil flat bottomed casserole large enough to hold rolled lasagna in one layer.
Pour 1/2-inch of the spaghetti sauce on bottom of casserole.
Halve lasagna noodles. Spread each with herb-cheese mixture (about 1/4 cup on each half). Roll up and place seam side down in casserole.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan.
Cover with foil. Bake covered with foil 20 minutes in a 350° oven, then uncover and bake until brown and bubbly, about 20 minutes more.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Chop tomatoes and boil until all to pieces.
Saute onion and sliced bacon together.
Put in pot with tomatoes.
If bacon makes too much grease, drain some off.
Cook about 5 minutes longer. Make thickening of milk and flour and add to soup.
Serve with cornbread.

title: shamrock parfaits
directions: In medium saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water; let stand 2 minutes to soften.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 3 minutes.
In small bowl, stir together sugar and cocoa; gradually add to gelatine mixture, stirring with whisk until well blended.
Continue to cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in evaporated milk and vanilla. Pour mixture in large bowl.
Refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon, about 20 minutes.
Fold 1/2 cup whipped topping into chocolate mixture. Divide about half of mixture evenly among 8 parfait or wine glasses.
Stir mint extract and food coloring into remaining topping and divide evenly among glasses.
Spoon remaining chocolate mixture over topping in each glass.
Garnish as desired. Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, relish and mustard.
Add ham.
Divide mixture among bagels.

title: sole fillet phyllo packets
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl. Stir well and set aside.
Place 1 sheet of phyllo on a damp towel (keep remaining phyllo covered).
Lightly coat phyllo with cooking spray. Fold in half crosswise.
Spread 1/4 of the cheese mixture across bottom 2-inches of phyllo; place 1 fillet on phyllo above cheese mixture. Fold cheese covered phyllo over fish.
Fold lengthwise edges in about 1-inch and roll up, jellyroll fashion.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Alternately add milk, flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Fold in remaining ingredients. (Don't let it rise until you put in oven.)
Keep in refrigerator, covered, until used.
When you are ready to cook, take from refrigerator and flour hands so you can shape into serving size balls.
Put into a greased pan, then into a hot oven of 425°.
Bake until a golden brown.
Smells delicious and tastes even better with honey or jam.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in half.
Seed and scoop out pulp.
Set pulp aside.
Heat oil in skillet.
Place tomatoes, cut side down, into oil.
Cook until the sides are carmelized.
Remove and place on a pastry sheet.
Add the butter to the skillet.
Saute the garlic and onion until tender.
Stir in seasonings and pulp.
Saute 1 more minute.
Fill tomato halves; sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in broiler until brown (about 2 minutes).

title: nutty cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients except walnuts in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add walnuts.
Makes 3 cups.
Serves 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma huffstetler's chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, flour, sugar and salt.
Combine milk and water. Add all the ingredients together except the flavoring.
Cook over medium-high heat until thick and smooth.
Cool.
Add the flavoring.
Pour into a baked pastry shell.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix cake as per directions on box.
Bake in 3 round cake pans and cool.
Mix milk and Jell-Os; add strawberries.
Pour 1/8 cup milk mixture into trifle bowl.
Layer, starting with cake and ending with Cool Whip.
Chill.
Better if made the night before.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add lemon juice and rind, milk and melted margarine.	Add
eggs
one at a time.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shell and
bake
at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: strawberry bread(two loaf pans)
directions: Blend all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until clean toothpick can be pulled out.
Sprinkle with xxxx sugar.
This freezes well.

title: carrot salad
directions: *I have found it works and tastes better to use about 3/4 cup of mayonnaise to 1 cup of chicken.

title: frankfurter noodle casserole
directions: Mix chopped green pepper and onion, prepared mustard and flour; simmer canned milk and salt in saucepan over low heat to just below boiling.
Add shredded Kraft American cheese; stir over low heat until the cheese melts.
Place cooked noodles in buttered 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Top with frankfurters; spread green pepper mixture over frankfurters.
Pour cheese sauce over all. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix together in bowl till crackers are coated.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 200° for about 15 minutes.
Stir; leave in oven for approx 5 minutes or more.
Remove; ready to eat. Store what's left in an air tight container.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make 4 thin layers from cake mix.
(Make according to directions on back of cake mix.)
Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream.
Let stand until sugar dissolves.
Mix 2 cups of Cool Whip with 1 cup of coconut mixture.
Set aside.
Spread coconut mixture between layers.
Put Cool Whip mixture on top and sides of cake. Keep in refrigerator.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Slice wieners into 1-inch pieces.
Put in crock-pot or heavy saucepan (large) over low heat.
Put in remaining ingredients. Stir.
Cook slowly for 1 to 2 hours.

title: peach tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add 3 tablespoons to cup with hot water.

title: zucchini fry cakes
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Add lemon juice, cheese, flour and onion.
Stir in zucchini.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fry until tender and browned.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and vanilla; blend well.
Add flour, mixing thoroughly.
Mix in pecans.
Shape into crescents and place on baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Carefully roll in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip sliced tomatoes into flour mixture.
Heat a small amount of oil in a skillet.
Fry tomatoes, turning once, until brown.

title: mrs. huey's jello
directions: Dissolve both boxes of jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Add bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch rectangle dish and chill until solid.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook the rice and dice	the chicken; add all the ingredients, except the Parmesan
cheese.
Put
cheese
on
top	of casserole. Bake at 350° for
to 45 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Simmer chicken, covered, in 2 cups of water until tender. Cool, debone and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Reserve 1 cup chicken broth.
Combine soups, onion, chilies and chicken broth.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch wide strips.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pickles for freezer
directions: Slice cucumbers thin and let stand in salted water for 2 hours.
Drain well.
Mix 1/2 cup white vinegar and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir well to dissolve sugar and heat to boiling, then cool.
Mix with pickles and onion rings.
Put in containers and freeze.
I pack the slices in 1-quart freezer bags, then pour in brine to cover.
Thaw when ready to use.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: pineapple raspberry punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Combine in a punch bowl.

title: beer pretzels
directions: Pour warm beer in a large mixing bowl and sprinkle with yeast and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Mix in flour and knead about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; cover and let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Pour over cooked shrimp.
To be really delicious, marinate shrimp for 4 to 5 hours. Serve cold on lettuce.
Makes 2 1/2 cups of sauce.
Serves 8.

title: stephanie's artichoke heart dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice hearts into bite size pieces. Combine mayonnaise and cheese in mixing bowl.
Add sliced hearts and mix well.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger with olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheeses) to hamburger.
Simmer sauce 1 hour.
Cook lasagne noodles as per package directions.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread a small amount sauce in bottom of pan, then layer noodles, sauce and cheeses.
End with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
